Patient  arrived to  Public Health Vaccination POD at the Fairgrounds for a Covid-19 vaccine on 4/10/2021. He received a dose of Janssen, Lot #1808982, in his left deltoid at 11:37am. In the car with him were 3 other adults/relatives who also received the vaccine and an infant in a car seat; Patient was the driver. After receiving the vaccine, patient pulled away from the table, reportedly became faint, briefly lost consciousness, and crashed his Jeep into the barricade at the side of the large garage door where he was attempting to exit. The Jeep sustained damage to the front passenger side. Medics were called to the scene. The first medic on the scene noted that Patient was diaphoretic and a noted an irregular pulse. Patients seat was reclined. Additional medics from ambulances in the parking lot arrived to the scene. Patient was put on a stretcher and taken to the ambulance. An IV was started and glucose level checked (result 98). Medics continued evaluation and patient was ultimately transported to Medical Center for further evaluation.
LAB_DATA: Blood glucose checked by medics with result of 98

After receiving her vaccine, patient moved into our waiting/observation area at my request to wait for 15 minutes of observation. Within a few minutes I heard the patient's mom calling out for help. I quickly ran over to help. I observed the patient who was now sitting on the floor. Her eyes were wide and she looked shocked. I helped her mother to calm patient and asked her to remain seated. I asked her mom what happened and she stated patient twitched a couple of times and began to fall off of her chair at which point mom caught her.  Mom had blood on her arm and I noticed it had come from patient's ear where a couple of earrings were pulled as she fell. I asked if she wanted water and quickly provided her a bottle of water. Mom stated that patient had fainted from vaccine(s) in the past, but mom stated that this appeared to look like a seizure. Mom went to get a chocolate bar since patient had had nothing to eat and they were worried about low blood sugar. After patient looked like she was back to normal I left to administer another vaccine but asked mom to remain until she felt necessary. Mom and patient advised my tech that they were ok and they left the store.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 4hrs of receiving the 2nd dose of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine I began to experience ringing in the ears followed by onset of extreme headaches and body aches somewhat dissimilar from the flu. These aches felt like painful internal construction of the head neck back and thigh muscles. Severe pain in the left arm where I received the jab.  I was extremely fatigued and could barely make it from bed to the bathroom. I treated the condition with Tylenol 1g every 4hrs followed by 200mg of Motrin. I also ensured adequate fluid hydration and electrolytes 120+ oz per day. The symptoms continued for about 36hrs. I began to feel better but 48hrs later I relapsed with the onset of ringing ears then headache followed by extreme fatigue. I treated the 2nd round with continued bed rest over 3 days with Tylenol (1g) and Motrin (400mg). I eliminated Tylenol day 2. I reduced Motrin to half on Day 3. I felt better for 48hrs and again relapsed but only needed smaller 200mg doses of Motrin for a day along with bed rest. The ringing in the ears have been consistent since the onset of the symptoms 4hrs after receiving the 2nd shot. The ringing is greater when I?m active and late in the day. The ringing in the ears is less after min of 6hrs full sleep during the night. I have yet to be able to exercise since racing that 2nd dose. I?m slowly progressing in reducing the fatigue by consuming 30mL shots of ginger juice daily along with 500mcg of  Vitamin B12 as directed by my Dr.
LAB_DATA: On 4/6/2021 I had a full CBC blood test that showed a lower B12 count of 285pg/ml so the Dr recommend taking 500mcg of B12 daily. I continue to suffer from the ringing in the ears and mild fatigue followed by mild to moderate headaches usually at the end of the day.

A pt came in to get a second dose of COVID-19 vaccine.  I usually verify the pt?s DOB and name then ask when and what kind of vaccines he/she received to be sure.  But I got distracted because, when I verified her DOB, she got upset since the tech who helped her didn?t fix her DOB.  I had to fix it myself.  Then when I came back, she told me she had a dental appointment.  I totally forgot to ask her what she had as her first dose and gave her Moderna since I only had the Moderna with me at that time.  When I tried to sign the COVID-19 Vaccination Record Card, I noticed that she received Pfizer-BioNTech.  I explained to her that she received Moderna by mistake.  I also told her that since both mRNA vaccine products are engineered with the same technology, she might not need to repeat the second dose.  And I observed her for about 30 minutes.  I told her that I would find out if she needed to repeat it.  I contacted the Immunization Action Coalition and they told me that as long as the pt had received mRNA COVID-19 vaccine products, pt would not need to repeat a dose.  They also sent me the CDC info on this recommendation.  But the CDC guideline is not clear to me since she received the two doses 21 days apart, not 28 days.  So I emailed a vaccine expert at the CDC, who I usually email whenever I have an immunization question.   I called the pt around 2 pm (two hours after vaccination) and she seemed to be doing fine at that time.   I gave her my cell phone number and told her to call me if she had any concerns.  I talked to her today and she told me that she called out since she was very tired.  I will follow up with her again.

After getting vaccine, I walked to the waiting area and sat down. After a few minutes my vision started getting strange and got worse for several minutes. In my peripheral vision I could see colors and patterns seeming to move and melt. Psychedelic. Very bad in my right eye, but also could see it in my left eye. Didn't check them by closing one, I was just trying to figure out what was happening to me. I could still read straight ahead. I stayed 10 minutes past my 15 min waiting period & felt well enough to leave. It probably took 1-2 hrs total before my vision seemed back to normal. No other symptoms after that. Researching on the internet I found kaleidoscope vision which seemed to describe it perfectly. Second dose did not produce any problems.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: leukemia; A PHASE 1/2/3, PLACEBO-CONTROLLED, RANDOMIZED, OBSERVER-BLIND, DOSE-FINDING STUDY TO EVALUATE THE SAFETY, TOLERABILITY, IMMUNOGENICITY, AND EFFICACY OF SARS-COV-2 RNA VACCINE CANDIDATES AGAINST COVID-19 IN HEALTHY INDIVIDUALS   This is a report from an interventional study source sponsored by BioNTech, managed and reported by Pfizer on the sponsor's behalf. The subject was in open-label phase of the study when the event occurred.   A 63-year-old male subject received blinded study vaccine (BNT162B2;PLACEBO) first dose on 29Aug2020 at 12:46 and second dose on 19Sep2020 at 09:12; the subject was unblinded to provide the opportunity of receiving COVID-19 vaccine per protocol and found to have received placebo. Then the subject received in open-label phase study vaccine BNT162B2, third dose on 11Jan2021 at 16:25 (Lot # P220395-020L) and fourth dose on 01Feb2021 at 16:06 (Lot# P220395-0068L), all via intramuscular (IM) route in left arm as single doses for COVID-19 immunization.  Ongoing medical history included diabetes mellitus type 2 from 1990, hypercholesterolemia from 2016, obesity from 2000, hypertension from 2010, sleep apnea from 2011, osteoarthritis knees from 2005, gastro esophageal reflux disease from 2018, coronary artery disease from 26Feb2021, worsening of elevated troponin level to 55 from 10Mar2021, productive cough from 01Mar2021. Additional medical history included pneumonia  from 18Feb2021 to 01Mar2021, non-ST elevation myocardial infarction on 26Feb2021 (AER 2021286057), coronary spasm from 08Mar2021 to 12Mar2021 (AER 2021286096), coronary blood stasis from 08Mar2021 to 12Mar2021 (AER 2021286096), elevated troponin level from 26Feb2021 to 10Mar2021. Family medical history relevant to adverse event included father-heart disease, mother-cancer, maternal grandmother-cancer, mother-osteoarthritis.  Ongoing concomitant medications included dulaglutide (TRULICITY) for diabetes mellitus type 2 from 2017, pravastatin for hypercholesterolemia from 2016, lisinopril for hypertension from 03Oct2020, dexlansoprazole (DEXILANT) for gastro esophageal reflux disease from 2018, fluticasone for seasonal allergies from 2017, cyanocobalamin for nutritional supplement from 2019, acetylsalicylic acid (ASPIRIN) for cardiovascular prophylaxis from 2015, vitamin D3 for nutritional supplement from 01Jan2021 and multivitamin for nutritional supplement from 2017. The subject had no concomitant vaccines or prior vaccinations (within 4 weeks).  The subject was diagnosed with leukemia on 18Mar2021, which was considered an important medical event and required a physician office and a visit to the emergency room. Clinical course was as follows: complete blood count (CBC) panel on 12Mar2021 (hospital discharge date for AER 2021286096) included:  white blood cell count (WBC) was 6.1 thousand/ul; cellular percentages were neutrophils 18%, lymphocytes 55%, monocytes 2%, basophils 0%, eosinophils 0 %, blasts 25% (low); absolute cell counts were absolute neutrophils 1098 cells/ul, low, absolute lymphocytes 3355 cells/ul, absolute monocytes 122 cells/ul, low, absolute basophils 0 cells/ul, absolute eosinophils 0 cells/ul, absolute blasts 1525 cells/ul; red blood cell count (RBC) was 2.81 million/ul (low), hemoglobin was 9.2 g/dl (low), hematocrit was 27.5% (low), mean cell volume (MCV) was 97.9 fl, mean cell hemoglobin (MCH) was 32.7 pg, mean cell haemoglobin concentration (MCHC) was 33.5 g/dl, red cell distribution width (RDW) was 14.7 %, platelet count was 129 thousand/ul (low), and mean platelet volume (MPV) was 9.5 fl.  Iron studies on 12Mar2021 were iron, total was 82 mcg/dl (low), iron binding capacity was 226 mcg/dl, % saturation was 38 mcg /dl, ferritin was 1396  ng/ml (high), and glucose was 163 mg/dl (high). Subject was referred to Oncology and had two bone marrow tests performed on 15Mar2021 and 25Mar2021. The doctors were testing the type of leukemia and the treatment options. Subject was scheduled to be admitted at hospital during the first week of April for 28 days. The action taken in response to the event for blinded study vaccine and study vaccine (BNT162B2) was not applicable (reported as dose not changed by the investigator). The outcome of the event was not recovered.   The investigator considered there was a reasonable possibility that the event leukemia was related to study vaccine (BNT162B2), while unrelated to blinded study vaccine, concomitant drugs or clinical trial procedure.; Sender's Comments: The event "Leukemia" is unlisted in the Single Reference Safety Document (SRSD) of the Investigational Product therapy vaccine (BNT162B2).  The company considers there is not a reasonable possibility that the event, leukemia, is related to vaccine administration based on the known adverse event profile of the suspect product and on the absence of a plausible pathophysiological mechanism by which the vaccine would be expected to cause this event.  Pfizer's safety database was reviewed for cases reporting PF-07302048 or blinded therapy through 15-MAR-2021 for adverse events encoding to MedDRA (v.23.1J) Preferred Term(s) of Leukaemia. Review of the database for the PT Leukaemia had the following results: 0 serious clinical trial cases (0 of which were attributed to therapy) and 2 non clinical trial cases.  The impacts of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product and on the conduct of the study is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committee and Investigators, as appropriate.

Immediately after receiving the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine the patient began to feel nauseous, hot and her arm was hurting. I kept her in the immunization booth and monitored her. Within a minute of her initial feeling she stated that she was having trouble seeing and was "going to black out". She immediately lost consciousness, her eyes rolled back, and her head went limp and fell back. She then began a twitching movement, made a snorting noise and then all of her limbs went rigid and extended straight out. At the first sign of her reaction we paged management and then as soon as she had loss of consciousness we contacted 911. She regained consciousness and was able to start answering my questions within 30 seconds to 1 minute. We did get the patient water and began to fan her to help cool her off. She was able to tell me who she was, where she was and why she was here. We also gave her some chips and had her eat slowly and drink small sips. She had stated that she was very nervous at the beginning of our pre immunization questions. She told us after that she had not eaten a lot before coming for the shot, but did eat more than normal because she knew she was coming in. She contacted her parents to inform them of the situation. She was able to recount everything prior to her loss of consciousness. When EMS arrived she was able to answer their questions. They took her vitals and all were in normal range, BP=119/66, pulse=98. They asked her to stand and she was able to stand and maintain balance on her own, but stated her legs felt a little "shaky". She refused transport to the hospital by EMS, but did call her roommate to come pick her up. I had her wait in the COVID waiting area until her roommate arrived. I called her around 4pm (same day) to check on her and she said she is feeling much better. Her mom (a nurse) also came down to stay with her and was with her when I called.
ALLERGIES: TREENUTS/PEANUTS: ANAPHYLAXIS; CEPHALOSPORINS: STEVEN JOHNSON SYNDROME

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had absolutely no symptoms prior to receiving the vaccination. After receiving the injection, I was directed to an extended 30 minute waiting area due to existing health conditions (MCAS). Within the first five minutes I began to feel strange pvc-like cardiac sensations in my chest (which I have not had for almost a year until now). Additionally, I began to feel quite dizzy, like I might pass out, and had immediate brain fog. I told the attending nurse that came to check on me and she called the on-site physician over to do a check up. I was told I seemed flushed on my chest and neck but I couldn't feel much at the time, so we weren't  sure if it was related. I was given a snack and water after the clinician asked if I may need to eat. I also took my afternoon beta-blocker a little early as a preventative measure. I began to feel quite hot and symptoms continued until the 30 minute window was up. My pulse was stable, however I was repeatedly asked if I wanted to call EMS services to the center (there weren't any on site due to time of day). I have had several episodes of severe brain fog and hot flashes.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Prior to receiving her COVID-19 vaccine, the patient was already having symptoms from anxiety/nervousness about the vaccine. Patient was given her injection and within 1-2 minutes, she began feeling dizzy and lightheaded. The vaccine administrator came to me (pharmacist on duty) to notify me that she was not feeling well. I went to go check on her and she stated that she felt as though she was going to faint. I advised her to stay seated, asked if she would like an ice pack and water, and stepped out to get those for her while remaining vigilant (because I wanted to be in the same room as her for observation/safety). I brought her the ice pack, she held it on her chest and head and said it felt nice. After about a minute I stepped out again to ask a technician to get a water for her. When I came back, the patient was still seated but had a blank stare and her mouth was slightly open. I repeated her name out loud and nudged her shoulder several times, however the patient was unresponsive completely. I immediately looked for the red emergency kit in the consultation room but did not see one (I later found out that there was an EpiPen on the table in the room, but I did not see it at the time due to the urgency of the situation). I rushed back into the pharmacy, told the technicians to call 911, and took an EpiPen off the shelf in the pharmacy. I ran back into the room and the patient's face was very red, her eyes were bulging slightly, and it looked like she was trying to reach her hand up or move it, but was unable to. I injected her with the EpiPen immediately, and within roughly 5 seconds she came back to consciousness and looked at me and said "I'm sorry". EMS arrived extremely fast and was there a few minutes after using the EpiPen. She was then taken by ambulance to the hospital. Patient had a friend, with her at the store who was scheduled to receive the vaccine as well, but after the incident she decided otherwise. Later that evening I gave patient's friend a phone call to check and see how patient was doing, and to also let her know that patient's vaccination card was at the pharmacy if she wanted to pick it up. That evening around 6:30-7pm, patient's husband came to the pharmacy to get her card, he updated us that she was being discharged from the hospital and that she was okay.

I was given the vaccine in the right upper arm.  I picked that arm due to PHN in my left trigininal nerve from shingles. They gave me the vaccine and I proceeded to move my car to the 30 minute waiting area. I put the car in park and suddenly I felt dizzy. Like I was looking through a magnifying glass backwards. Since I have a reaction to Xolair in 12/15/2021 I had been extra cautious. This hit my quickly. It felt like I had a ton of weight on my chest. It progressed quickly to where I felt like I couldn't breath. The staff was watchful. They called an ambulance.  They monitored me there but it was like I could not wake up. I wanted to fall asleep. My blood pressure was higher than normal at one point during my ER visit I looked up and my blood pressure was 137/91. I felt like I had when I had a many stroke in 2019 my speech was slower I couldn't get the words out. My toes and finger were cold. They transported me to the ER for observation. It was that that the head ache only in my right frontal lobe started and my arm and neck on the right side began to hurt. Within about 1.5 hours I began to wake up from the fog and my speak cleared up. While laying on the bed my fingers were curling up. As the speech returned that hands warmed up.and my fingers began to release. The staff at the clinic had given me benadryl within about 20 minutes of the vaccine.  Upon release I was droggy and like a huge adrenal rush had worn off. I had slight stuffy nose and like I had a severe hay fever reaction that I was coming down from last night. This hit me quick and hard. The ER said I had a stress reaction and a head ache of unknown cause as all of my blood work came back normal. But honestly at one point I felt paralyzed. Even today I feel stuffier than I normally do. Like I have a slight asthma attack.  I know my blood oxygen was 97 % at one point and I can tell when it drops even a precent
LAB_DATA: There was a gaint list that were done on 04/09/2021 at the Medical center
OTHER_MEDS: Concerta Advair Lorastan Potassium Amplodipine Levothyroxine Allegra Valtrex Ozempic
CUR_ILL: Shingles reoccurring Oestoathritis came on one month after discontinued xolair
HISTORY: Thyroid Asthma Allergies Reoccurring shingles High blood pressure

Patient got the Jansen covid 19 vaccine today.  She waited 30 minutes (since she stated she got a rash as a kid from a vaccine and hadn't received a vaccine since then).  She was fine after 30 minutes and handed us the timer and walked away.  She came back and said she thought she is just hungry since she hadn't eaten and felt funny.  She said she was going to get some food.  We had associate walk her over.  They came back.  She sat down and ate her food.  We checked on her but now she stated she had vertigo and needed meclizine and thought she'd be ok if she went home and laid down. I offered her ice for her neck or head and she refused.  I also offered to lay her on the floor and elevate her feet, but she refused.  She said her neck gives her problems so didn't want ice or to lower her neck. She was sitting this whole time and said she felt in slow motion.  She said she wanted to go to the restroom but I didn't want her going alone. She called her son in law that was shopping in the store and we asked him to come over.  He was going to drive her home but she said no one was home.  I asked if they'd like an ambulance and they both said yes.  We called 911 and stayed with the patient until EMS arrived.  She was feeling somewhat better but they took her to get checked out to be safe.

One hour after the shot, I felt a choking sensation at the top of my throat/back of my mouth. This happened right after I drank water for the first time after the shot. My father looked in my throat and said it was my uvula, which was enlarged and swollen. I also had a lot of red streaks and veins on my uvula and throat, similar to what it looks like in your eye when you have conjunctivitis. I could swallow, talk, and eat, so we did not go to the ER. However, this choking sensation and swelling did not dissipate at all for 13 days. I could technically eat, but I often didn?t because it was painful. I also had a tight heavy chest and was exhausted after small movements. After a week, a nurse suggested taking Benadryl and Pepcid for two days. I didn?t feel any difference, so I went to urgent care. A covid test was negative. The doctor there said to consult UAB and the CDC before getting the second shot because he was not sure if it was an allergic reaction. I have not been able to get in contact with anyone from either place. My symptoms sometimes go away and I get some relief now, but it hasn?t gone away completely. I would really appreciate some help in making the decision to take the second shot. It is scheduled for April 15 and I have been desperately asking for someone to call me. I?ve left a message on the CDC?s phone line. The UAB hospital just tells me to call the CDC. The state health dept said I should have the second shot administered inside a hospital instead of the drive-thru but did not help me get this arrangement. I am on my own with no advocate and I am disabled. The process of getting the first shot also contributed to what seemed to be an increase in sensory processing difficulties that are part of ASD.
ALLERGIES: Not sure, but odd reactions and intolerances to grains, dairy, soy, some preservatives and such. Family allergies to penicillin are so common that I just don?t usually take it.

The shot was administered by a young woman at pharmacy, who I later learned was an intern. She injected the shot less than two fingers down from my shoulder bone, much higher than I have ever had an injection given before.  I immediately felt intense pain, and the intern had trouble pushing the syringe down fully.  She said ?I need help!?, and her male manager ran over, and quickly jabbed the syringe further into my arm, and pressed extremely hard down on the syringe, forcing the remaining contents into my arm. I immediately felt a shooting, searing pain down my entire arm, into my wrist, and  my arm went numb, felt heavy, and tingly by my hand.  The manager pulled the needle out of my arm, and said ?you must have hit bone, the needle is bent?.  I then felt extremely nauseous and woozy, and my vision started going in and out.  I fanned myself and after about five minutes my vision stabilized, and I felt less nauseous.  It is now 9 hours later and I have intense shoulder and neck pain, and limited range of motion of my shoulder.
LAB_DATA: I called the insurance company nurses hotline at around 1pm EST on 4/10/21, and they advised that I visit an urgent care.  I visited the Urgent Care at 3pm on 4/10/21.  They advised that I keep monitoring the shoulder pain over the next few weeks, and prescribed lidocaine patches.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: When I smile, only the right side of my face reacts. The left side of my face does not react at all. I thought I had a stroke, so I went to the emergency room after two days of being unable to move the left side of my face. They diagnosed it as Bell's palsy and prescribed prednisone (deltasone), 10 Mg tablets for 9 days.
LAB_DATA: The hospital conducted a CT scan just on my head to determine whether I had a stroke. They did tests where I had to squeeze the doctor's hands and other tests to assess whether I had a stroke. They looked in my eyes and at my tongue. They determined that I did not have a stroke.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: February 17, 2021:  Patient received 1st dose of PfizerBioNTech vaccine.  Reported mild cough, nausea and bone pain lasting one week. However, she felt it wasn't severe enough to contact me as her asthma specialist.  No cough per patient for the week prior to the second dose of PfizerBioNTech. March 10, 2021:  Patient received 2nd dose of PfizerBioNTech vaccine at 1:10pm.  Said she had mild chest tightness during the waiting period and used her Ventolin but she attributed it to the characteristics of the waiting room area.  Between 5:00pm and 6:00pm (~4 hours later), she became light-headed, vomited and began to cough frequently.  She contacted her primary care physician who told her to use Mucinex and contact me if needed. March 12, 2021:  Patient contacted my office in the early afternoon.  Unable to stop coughing while on telephone.  Came to office approximately 90 minutes later.  Physical Exam;  Peak Flow 210 (personal best 310-320), oxygen saturation 93-95% (typically 97-98%), temp-98.2 F.  Intractable cough with scattered bilateral expiratory wheezes on auscultation.  Heart rate 132 and regular.  Patient treated with Levalbuterol 1.25 mg nebulization with subsequent modest improvement in frequency of cough, pulse 102, oxygen saturation 96-97%.  She declined going to emergency department of hospital because she did not want to get infected with COVID-19 from a patient in the waiting room.  She declined Prednisone when told that the corticosteroid might reduce the efficacy of the 2nd dose of the vaccine.  Placed on Budesonide 1 mg bid and Levalbuterol 1.25 mg q4-6h prn. March 16th:  Patient reported her cough was 70% improved and wanted to stop Budesonide.  Patient was told to continue Budesonide daily at 1 mg q day. April 5th:  Patient contacted my office because of continued coughing and wheezing.  Had been hospitalized March 25-27 for the cough.
LAB_DATA: March 27:  CT Chest--no interstitial lung disease, + right upper lob nodular opacity.
OTHER_MEDS: Allegra, Singulair, Ventolin 1prn, Benadryl 25 mg qhs, Asacol, Enalapril, Mestinon, Salonpas patch, Anacin, Tramadol, Acyclovir prn, Klorcon prn, Citracal prn, Vitamin D, Vitamin C, Amlodipine, Levothyroxine, Natural Tears, Systane, Mylanta
CUR_ILL: No acute illnesses up to one month prior.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient was administered Janssen COVID vaccine. Patient had blood dripping from forehead and nose. Gauze was applied to laceration on forehead to help with bleeding and once patient was able to roll over on his back, an ice pack was applied to his forehead/nose area. Patient said he felt "pain" after the injection and then he felt light-headed. He remembered blacking out for a few seconds. Patient stated he felt "ok", then later stated he felt better but just had a bad headache. Patient stated he felt "it starting to hurt" and that it triggered his anxiety. Dad was in the store and arrived a few minutes later; dad said son/patient has a "fear of needles" and "he hasn't had anything to eat today in quite awhile". EMS arrived to examine patient and asked him if he needed to go to the ER; dad felt going to the ER was for the best since they had a 3 hour car ride home. Paramedics then transported patient to the ER and said he would likely need a stitch for the cut above his eyebrow.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 3:00am-4:00am I woke up with extreme chills. And it felt as if my blood flowing was cold. I had a fever of 100.8 F .... My migraine came a few hours later after I slept for another two hours so around 630am and I was told not to take ibuprofen or aspirin. I used a cool rag to cover my eyes and that helped my head pounding as well as helped lower my fever a little bit it was 100 F around 8am .... Through out the day Friday it was as if my symptoms spiked and got worst before they got better. Lymph nodes on side of the injection site were very swollen and tender. My muscles and body was aching pretty badly. I felt very weak and extremely tired. I slept almost all of Friday away, it was hard to get out of bed and bc I was so weak and tired and slept so so long, I was not keeping myself hydrated and that def made it worse. My fever has remained between 100-102(at it's highest) ... Today is Saturday and around 3-4am on Sunday will make 48 hours since the symptoms began. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 2:30pm, on 4/3/21, I started developing very bad lower back pain, which made it very uncomfortable to stand or sit. Twelve hours after receiving my 2nd Pfizer dose, I developed strong flu-like symptoms including 102 degree temp, whole-body aches, whole-body muscle aches, alternating chills and hot spells, a RAGING whole-head headache that radiated down the back of my neck. The top of my scalp hurt, even my skin hurt. For 60+ hours these symptoms continued and my temperature bounced between 99.9 and 102. I self-treated with Tylenol 500mg every 6 hours; midway I switched to Alka Seltzer Severe Cold and Flu every 4 hours. I could not sleep due to the relentless headache which the OTC meds did not touch. Once the body aches began to subside after 60 hours, the RAGING headache continued. By 72 hours, the worst had passed ; today, 5 days after the 2nd dose, I am extremely fatigued. I have no regrets about getting vaccinated, but I felt this was an extreme response to the vaccine. For what it's worth, in March 2020, just as COVID was taking off  I tested positive for Influenza A, but I suspected I also had COVID. I had all the symptoms the news was reporting, loss of taste and smell, fever, difficulty breathing, cough, ETREME fatigue and weakness in my legs, sore throat, nausea & vomiting and diarrhea. The cough, shortness of breath and extreme fatigue continued for WEEKS. But there were no tests for COVID at that point. Twelve weeks after I  began to recover from the flu event, my doctor discouraged me from having the antibody test, because at that point the tests were not widely available nor very accurate.

Tachycardia.    I was injected on 4-3-21 at 2:15 pm in the left arm.  I was instructed to wait 30 minutes due to my given history of anaphylactic events.  I took one 25 mg Benadryl  and one 180 mg of Allegra one hour prior to the shot due to this history.  I was released at 2:45 pm and felt fine.  I went home and sat on the sofa to watch tv.  I sat there a couple of hours and thought I would take a nap since it was Saturday.  At 5:50 pm I felt my heart begin to race and could see the veins on the back of my hands pulsing and my jacket I still had on moving/jumping to my heart beat. I could hear and feel my heart beating too fast.  I got the pulse-ox meter that my husband has since he is an EMT and measured my resting heart rate to be 161 bpm.  It frightened me as the only other time my heart raced like that was during two other anaphylactic events.   I took 50 mg of Benadryl, got my epipens from my pocketbook and tried to breathe slowly and calmly.  After about 40 minutes my heart rate slowed to 125 bpm.  It took about two hours to reach a normal rate around 79 bpm.  I had it fluctuate all evening but not as high as 161 bpm.  I took more Benadryl as I went to bed.  The next morning my resting heart rate was between 90-115 bpm off and on through lunch time.
LAB_DATA: Due to premedicating with Benadryl and then taking more once the event started, I did not have to use my Epipen and therefore did not seek medical care.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient was sitting in observation area 5 minutes post vaccination, scheduled to be observed for 30 minutes total due to history of anaphylaxis. She was seated in the recliner She reported to have itchy watery eyes, chest tightness.  Breath sounds were clear, with good air movement bilaterally, no wheezing or crackles, no accessory muscle use, normal speech. Patient's boyfriend noted her tongue and eyelids to appear slightly swollen compared to baseline. Patient denied dizziness, chest pain, shortness of breath, body rash or itching. Patient maintained normal speech and normal unlabored respirations.  BP was checked and noted to be normal. O2 sat 99%. Patient received  benadryl 50mg PO. She was observed for about 10 minutes before her tongue appeared more swollen and she complained of difficulty breathing. At this point, the patient appeared pale, 911 was activated. EPI-pen was administered via autoinjector in the left lateral thigh. O2 sat was 99%. Patient has increased chest tightness and new onset shortness of breath for which she was given an Albuterol nebulizer. Breath sounds were clear, no wheezing. O2 sat reassessed which decreased to 73%, she had bilateral cramping of hands and digits. Non-rebreather was applied, oxygen saturation improved and hand cramps resolved. 911 was called for a second time to report rapid desaturation. Patient's O2 saturation and HR fluctuated, BP remained stable throughout. EMS arrived. A right AC IV was placed, Solumedrol 125mg IVP was administered by EMS. Patient was transferred onto EMS stretcher, still requiring nonrebreather. Patient was escorted to ED for further management of anaphylxis post Moderna vaccine.

SHE DECLINED ANYTHING I ASKED HER (TO LAY DOWN, TO GET HER A COLD WASHCLOTH). SHE STATED SHE THOUGHT SHE WAS JUST NERVOUS ABOUT THE VACCINE, AS SHE WAS EXTREMELY NERVOUS TO GET IT. AFTER A FEW MORE MINUTES SHE ASKED FOR US TO CALL AND AMBULANCE. SHE STATED SHE JUST WANTED TO BE CHECKED OUT TO MAKE SURE SHE WAS OK AND THAT SHE DID NOT WANT TO DRIVE UNTIL SHE WAS. SHE STILL SAID HER BREATHING WAS FINE, AND THAT SHE DID NOT FEEL LIKE SHE WAS GOING TO PASS OUT.  SHE DID THEN TELL ME THAT HER HEART FELT LIKE IT WAS BEATING FAST BUT THAT WAS EARLIER ON AND THAT IT HAD STOPPED. EMTS ARRIVED. I CALLED HER THE SAME DAY TO FOLLOW UP  AND SHE WAS HOME AND FELT FINE. SHE HAD BEEN GIVEN ATIVAN IN THE HOSPITAL TO CALM HER DOWN.  SHE STATED THE HOSPITAL SAID THEY DID NOT KNOW IF IT WAS HER NERVES OR A REACTION TO THE VACCINE.

HPI: PT 28 y/o F feeling light headed after J&J vaccination.  PT with her mother, became light-headed and dizzy while walking from vaccination site back to vehicle for 15 minute wait. PT became unresponsive with mother and fainted.  Parking staff alerted rapid response team, PT regained responsiveness and was given chair to sit on, water to drink.  Rapid response team arrived to a responsive, A&Ox4, pale female who was still feeling weak and light-headed.  PT was transferred to a cot (in the shade) where she was placed in supine position with legs elevated on a chair.  Pt was given water and hard candy to suck on while vitals were taken,,  Airway, breathing and circulation were all WNL.     PT states she presently has a strep infection (throat area)  and has been afebrile, and is to begin oral antibiotics once she picks RX up from pharmacy.     PT began feeling significantly better over 10-15 minutes of laying down in the shade.    EMS LAFD was called and transfer of care to EMS Station 93 for further work-up was instituted.  PT felt much better and was able to stand and ambulate from cot to EMS vehicle without issue.    PT chose to go home with her mother instead of being transported by EMS to medical facility.      Exam (update as needed): GEN: Alert and oriented x 4, relaxed in appearance. HEAD: WNL EYES: PERRL, EOMI ENT: Ears normal, Nose normal, OP normal, no evidence of angioedema, no cyanosis  NECK: Supple, without LAD.  CV: RRR, no m/r/g
LAB_DATA: Care transferred to LAFD EMS where PT was evaluated and chose not to be transferred, signing AMA form.  PT was feeling much better,
CUR_ILL: HX of strep infection (throat)  Endometriosis - acute
PRIOR_VAX: PT states she has a HX of feeling 'light-headed' and dizzy with vaccinations

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came to Vaccine POD to receive first dose of Pfizer vaccine (LOT #ER8731, Expires 07/2021) on 4/10/2021. Patient has a medical history of hypertension and has allergies to ibuprofen and penicillin. Patient received approval from her doctor and specialists to receive Pfizer vaccine. The patient gave verbal consent to receive the Pfizer vaccine and was vaccinated at 1459 by RN. The patient was given an observation time of 30 minutes with RN, who was performing the EMT observer role on site. At 1530, the patient reported experiencing "tingling" in her lips and tongue. Lead RN was called to assist with the patient. The patient presented with redness localized on face. The patient was assisted to anti-gravity chair at 1531. At 1532, the patient's vitals were taken by RN: BP 160/90, HR 83 BPM, RR 21/min. RN administered 50mg/1mL Benadryl IM in the patient's right arm at 1537. The patient denied difficulty breathing. The patient's vitals were reassessed every 5 minutes for 30 minutes. The patient remained A&Ox4 throughout 30 minute observation period. The patient's vitals at 1538 were: BP 200/118, HR 88 BPM, RR 22/min. The patient states she forgot to take her blood pressure medication in the morning. She states her baseline blood pressure is around 160 systolic. At 1543, the patient's vitals were: BP 160/102, HR 90 BPM, RR 22/min. Visibly, the patient was less flushed. Patient was able to look at herself through her cell phone camera and pallor returned to normal limits, per patient. At 1548, the patient's vitals were: BP 155/108, HR 83 BPM, RR 20/min. At 1553, the patient's vitals were: BP 160/102, HR 79 BPM, RR 18/min. The patient states the tingling in her lips and tongue has resolved. The patient sat up with her feet dangling below her, her vitals were as follows: BP 167/110, HR 79 BPM, RR 17/min. The patient reported "feeling better" and requested to drive herself home. RN provided patient with education about side effects of Benadryl, including fatigue. Patient states she is unable to find a ride and must drive herself home. Patient states she is "feeling fine" and lives "3 minutes away". The patient was given education related to when to seek medical care, including shortness of breath, chest tightness, and sensation of throat tightness. The patient demonstrates understanding of teaching and states she will call her doctor if her symptoms worsen. The patient's gait was steady and patient denied any dizziness or lightheadedness. At 1601, the patient requested to drive herself home. She was escorted to her car by RN. Upon departure, patient was ambulatory, A&Ox4, with no reports of trouble breathing, dizziness, or lightheadedness. Patient drove herself home AMA at 1604.

Patient is a 57-year-old female with a history of ADHD, on Adderall, who presented to the ED complaining of rash starting 2 days prior to presentation.  It started on her nose and shifted to her bilateral malar area and then went to her left ear and, on the day of presentation, spread to her left arm.  It is non-itchy, nonpainful.  She denies any open wounds, shortness of breath, wheezing, dysphagia.  She took the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine 1st dose on March 24, 2021.  She did have prior elevated ANA value and was undergoing investigation for autoimmune disease.  There is no formal diagnosis yet.  She also states that she has been taking care of her grand baby who seems to have had a viral illness with diarrhea.  She herself denies fever, but does complain of a cough.  The baby tested negative for COVID-19.  Patient, initially, presented to Centra Care and had been taking Bactrim, Bactroban and Medrol Dosepak with no relief. Patient's rash nearly completely resolved after IV benadryl, solumedrol, and Pepcid in the hospital. She initially had hyperkalemia, likely due to Bactrim, that resolved after kayexalate.

I received the J&J vaccine on 3/24, and by that evening I had a headache, and my tinnitus was louder than normal. I had mild barely perceptible tinnitus prior to the vaccine. I would normally never notice it during the day, but lying down and going to sleep in a quiet room I would hear it. Constant high pitch but not loud, in the background more. I always run a fan in my bedroom so that I have some white noise and don't hear it. I had the flu like headache from the vaccine for two days and then it slowly started to subside into the weekend. I was tired as well from the immune response.  Five days out, I get out of the shower in the morning, and go to put underarm deodorant on, and notice my left armpit is all bright red. I check my right armpit, just as red.. Took photos of the red armpits and shared with some family and friends, as I read on the Internet that there were all kinds of crazy side effects that were possible. The red skin like rash is one of them, although my armpits never itched or burned. I could feel that they were warmer than normal, that was it. It was the 2nd day after my red armpits that my tinnitus ratcheted up to the current level that I am really unhappy with. The red armpits went away within 48 hours, never did anything about the redness, just didn't put underarm deodorant on until it passed. Sadly, the Tinnitus has remained and it is at a level that is distracting and persistent.
LAB_DATA: I am just past two weeks since the vaccine, and was hoping the Tinnitus would subside. I am going to contact my doctor, have a physical, blood work done, see an ENT, whatever is recommended.

Patient received second dose of Pfizer-BioNtech Covid-19 vaccine today and after 5-7 minutes reported to a pharmacy technician she was feeling nauseous. Patient wanted to keep her head down because she experienced light sensitivity; I placed cold compresses on her neck. Patient worsened over the next 10 minutes, complaining of feeling dizzy, anxious, intense headache. At this time, 15 minutes after being vaccinated, I (the vaccinating pharmacist) moved the patient to a private booth to have her lie down on the floor with her feet elevated. The patient was able to communicate the entire time and called her relatives to come pick her up from work. Emergency services were called as the patient was not experiencing anaphylaxis, but was increasingly more anxious and was afraid she'd fall or faint. Emergency medical services arrived after the patient had been laying down with feet elevated for almost 30 minutes. Patient did not complain of trouble breathing but did request use of her inhaler. Patient did not state on her patient questionnaire and consent form that she has asthma; she mentioned this during her episode. Patient was taking to a local hospital.

I had COVID in early December. During this time I lost my taste and smell and it came back two weeks later.   After receiving my first vaccine, I had the normal symptoms of someone receiving their second shot. I've read this is common among younger people who have previously had COVID. I had two days of fever and chills, but that's not why I'm report this.  My taste and smell has been altered since the day after my vaccine. For weaker smells, I don't pick them up at all. Stronger smells either smell excessively sweet or burnt. I can pick up about 20% of the smell of something and the other 80% is this weird sweet or burnt flavor, but never both. Garbage, gasoline, hand sanitizer all have the same sweet smell. Most food smells burnt.  My taste is similar. Some food has a burnt flavor. Beef, previously a favorite food of mine, has a nauseating taste to it that prevents me from eating too much of it.   I have read that some people are experiencing post-COVID parosmia, but given that mine came on immediately after my vaccine I can't help but wonder if there is a correlation. It's been nearly a month without much improvement.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my 2020/2021 flu vaccine while at work on the night of 11/18/2020 at 9pm. Immediately upon receiving the vaccine, I experienced flushing/hot feeling in my face & neck & had severe abdominal pain. I left work at 10pm and went right to bed since I was feeling ill. At 3am, I awoke from the severe abdominal pain I was still experiencing. I went to my kitchen & passed out on my hard wood floor. I awoke in extreme vertigo with nausea & vomiting. After about 2 hrs, my husband called an ambulance because I was unable to lift my head up and I was still experiencing severe vertigo with nausea/vomiting. I was transported to the hospital and treated in the ER (X-ray, basic blood work, etc.) I was admitted for 23 hr observation. I had an MRI and was started on Meclizine 25mg oral three times a day. I was evaluated by neurology during my admission. Upon discharge, I went to my PCP because I was still in vertigo. He referred me to a vestibular PT for treatment to reset my ear crystals. I was treated three times by the vestibular physical therapist. My vertigo resolved after 3 weeks. I was unable to work for 3 weeks. It was believed that I experienced a concussion from my fall.
LAB_DATA: MRI -10/19/2020 -within normal limits BMP- normal X-ray (head & spine)-10/19/2020 - normal

Patient given Pfizer vaccine at 4:34 pm, several minutes later approximately 4:40 pm this provider was alerted by other staff member to report to waiting room where patient was waiting post-vaccination. Patient was being supported by other staff member and mother against the wall due to him not being able to support himself. Patient was semi-conscious but responsive at this time. With the help of this provider, mother and other staff member, patient was gently lowered to floor and laid in supine position, head was supported and assisted with elevating his legs. Shortly after patient responded that he was feeling much better then attempted to try and sit up but started to feel lightheaded and was then assisted with laying back in supine position. Patient's pulse and blood pressure was checked. At 4:45pm pulse was at 38 BPM and then at 4:47 pm 55 BPM and blood pressure at 90/60.  This provider then alerted other staff member to call EMS due to abnormal vital signs. EMS did arrive shortly after and then patient was assessed per EMS. Patient was stabilized and elected to not go to hospital. Patient left with mother to go home at approximately 5:01 pm.

Husband was driving, he got his vaccine at the same time, I was on passenger side. Within  one minute of injection, my head felt really funny, underside of lower arm started itching (the itching went away within a minute or so), chest tightened and felt light headed. Got out of vehicle for some fresh air, was told if dizzy, sit down.  Got back in vehicle and blasted AC and leaned into vent to breathe.  Wave of awful lightheadedness came in spurts, but have NEVER reacted to any other vaccine like this, I convinced myself it must be low blood sugar, even though I tested fine before I left.  I was not nervous, and was in fact, excited to get this vaccine.   After 15 minutes, we leave, grab a bite to eat.  The lightheadedness came in waves and just didn't stop. An hour after, I started sweating and my heart was  switching between what seem like rapid pulse to pounding heartbeat, to the point I could hear it in my ears and when I laid down, it felt like my veins vibrated.  Around 5:30, a friend took me to the ER.  Having had to wait a while, thankfully by the times my vitals were took, everything looked normal.  Was told it was a panic attack and to get the second vaccine. That makes no sense, as I was not anxious and this was a very physical reaction.

I got the vaccine at 3:45 arm was sore but I wasn?t worried Later that night around 6 I started feeling disgusting from vaccine so I took an Advil.  Around 8-10pm my body started getting chills, I started shaking, I had a headache my muscles were sore, and I started getting a fever. Around 12am all of the previous symptoms got worse my fever was at about 101 and rising and I was extremely tired. At 1am I felt the worst I have ever felt in my entire life. I could barely walk because my muscles and joints hurt and my fever was over 102.5 and I felt like my veins were on fire. At 2 am I moved to my bathroom because the floor was cold and I didn?t want my roommate seeing me cry from how much pain I was in. I have a high pain tolerance but this was the worst pain I?ve ever been in. In the bathroom I was at the peak of the pain of the vaccine. My fever was over 103 all of my previous side effects were worse than ever I felt weak and a little dizzy. I also was having a hard time breathing, my breathing was weak and I felt like I wasn?t getting enough air. I tried looking up on my phone if I should go to the hospital but I could barely pick up my phone to type or look. I dropped my phone and fell asleep in the floor for 20 minutes before I woke up. I walked slowly over to my bed and took a Tylenol and then had a sip of water and felt like I was going to puke. I tried to use my inhaler and I couldn?t hold my breath to use it. I crawled into bed and slept until 11 the next day and was too sore to walk to class all of my joints still hurt and I had a fever of 101 and a headache . I took a Tylenol and around 6pm my fever broke and I was feeling better. The next day I was still too sore to walk to class and had a headache. Today I am still sore but better my lungs still feel a little tight, I feel unfocused , and I still feel dizzy occasionally. I have no appetite and I feel nauseous when I eat so I?ve been eating in smaller portions . Every single day since the shot I?ve felt very tired. I hope these symptoms get better and Looking back on the night of vaccine I should have gone to the hospital.

I ended up in the ER where they gave me an anti inflammatory shot.  I went home and continued taking a high dose of over the counter anti inflammatory  for 3 days until my stomach couldn't handle it. I had breathing difficulty for 9 days with tremendous fatigue, I am a high energy person normally. For 9 days I also had high blood pressure whenever I was on my feet for 30 minutes or more. I had a lot of nausea, dizziness, and a deep headache. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I experienced a slight headache  sore arm and elevated blood pressure after the shot. My blood pressure is usually very well controlled. On Monday the 29th, at about 3:30 pm, I started to slur my words. At first we blamed it on the Novocaiine earlier in the day, but I had been talking fine after it and had had it many, many times before and it was worn off. We called my doctor's office after my right arm and leg became very heavy and awkward. They told me to go to the nearest hospital. When I got there, I presented ass a full stroke. I was very hard to understand and my mouth drooped and I had very little use of my right arm and leg. They ran tests, but could not give me the medication because I was already on Eliquis. They thought they saw a small clot very high up. I was hospitalized over the next four days and improved my speech dramatically after a bad headache on March 30. The doctors go back and forth to whether it was a Acute Ischemic Stroke, which is what my paperwork says and a complex migraine. I do not experience migraines or anything like this ever before.  I did not have a real headache on the 29th. Since my symptoms, right arm and leg difficulties are still here, my Doctor believes it was a stroke. I have an appointment with a Neurologist and I have to have another MRI. I am going to Physical Therapy. My Doctor told me to fill this out, she thinks it may be from the vaccine.

The evening after I received my vaccine I became very cold and couldn't get warm, to the point of shivering very hard, while at the same time having a fever of 102 F (about 9:30 pm).  The house was 68 F, and I bundled up with thermal underwear, fleece pajamas, a robe, and two extra blankets, but I couldn't stop feeling cold.  My body was painfully sore the rest of the night; this may have been a reaction from shivering so hard and wearing my muscles out.  Later that night, I woke up in a sweat (maybe 11:30pm) and had to strip out of my clothes down to my underwear, and I couldn't stop feeling warm.  I slept the rest of the night on top of the covers, and woke up very frequently, probably every half hour.  Each time I woke, I drank half a glass of water (about 6 oz).  The next day my fever was gone and I felt normal temperature wise, but my muscles were all very sore.  I had flu-like symptoms for about a week, a little bit less each day.  It was probably a full week later until I felt normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 24 hours after the second vaccine shot I had fever 99.1.  Chills with muscle soreness between my shoulder blades and lower back at hip level. These symptoms lasted about ten hours. I took Tylenol immediately after the shot and then about six or seven  hours apart  after the first dose.  The injection sight was swollen and itchy for several days. On 6 April the injection site bled and then scabbed over, continuing to itch until 8 April.

At 5:05 am on April 11, approx. 37 hours after I received the shot, I awakened to a rapid muscle convulsion in my left shoulder muscle, at the approximate location of the injection. I counted between 2 to 6 contractions per second (yes, it was a very quick twitch that involved my whole upper arm). It went on for at least 10 minutes, then paused for less than a minute and then resumed. This was a pronounced muscle spasm which I cannot remember having before. I have had twitching eyelids or facial muscle that would twitch for a few minutes in the past, but this went on for over 30 minutes, and I am not sure it is done. Also, this was much more intense than the above-referenced twitches. The location and time relative to my shot makes me fairly certain that this is an effect of the vaccine. I have not exercised or done anything to cause this to my knowledge. Of course, this seems like a harmless side effect, but my concern is that my heart muscle reacting to this in a similar fashion could be more serious.
OTHER_MEDS: Famotidine 40 mg 1-daily, supplements_ vitamin c, vitamin d, vitamin e, zinc, glucosamine/condroitin joint supplements

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 30 seconds of the injection of my second dose of Moderna, I experienced extreme nausea unlike any that I have experienced before. Within 1 minute of the injection, my face, arms, chest, and neck flushed and I turned completely red. I felt hot and started to sweat. At the same time, I began having trouble breathing with the sensation that my throat was beginning to close. My eyes filled with tears and I was not able to talk to communicate what was happening. My mom, who was with me at the time of vaccination, asked the administering pharmacist if I could remove my mask because I was having trouble breathing. Throughout this reaction, the pharmacist froze and was visibly in shock of what was happening. Because of this, my mom began asking me questions to figure out what else I was experiencing. Once I was able to remove the mask and breathe deeply, the reaction subsided after two minutes. The pharmacist, after my reaction began to subside, stated that they had an epipen ready to administer if needed. I was never administered the epipen. The pharmacist asked me to wait 30 minutes instead of the general 15 minutes before leaving the site. Because the symptoms went away and did not return within the 30 minutes, I left the site. After the vaccination, I experienced a low-grade fever for 79 hours, chills, a headache, muscle aches, and extreme fatigue. After realizing my reaction was not considered ?normal,? I began to research and realized these symptoms align with anaphylaxis, even though they subsided quickly after experiencing them.
OTHER_MEDS: Hydration packets including Drip Drop and Liquid IV taken leading up to the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received vaccine and was instructed to sit for 15 minutes as required for monitoring. About five minutes in, another patient who received the vaccine together with patient told us the patient had fainted. Patient was slumped over to the side when I came to check on patient. I called the patient a few times and patient started to come to. I asked the patient how he was feeling and if he had any difficulty breathing to assess for anaphylactic shock. Patient was breathing normal, but was sweating and a bit confused. Patient reported feeling dizzy. I explained to patient that he fainted for a few minutes and instructed to sit as I did not feel comfortable having patient lay down in the state he was in. Patient was given water and a fan to help cool him down and legs elevated (patient reported feeling much better with the fan blowing on him). Patient sat at the pharmacy for over 30 minutes before heading to the bathroom. At this point, patient were no longer dizzy and I instructed him to get up slowly and assessed that patient was no longer dizzy before letting him go to the bathroom.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Severe muscle spasms from muscle scarring from an accident 20 years ago.  See earlier accident history for more details.
HISTORY: About 20 years ago I flipped an ATV and my stomach went skidding across the ground and tearing my  abs muscles.  For at least a year they would tense up and be tender constantly.  I had Skelaxin which worked, but I ran out after the first month and suffered for the rest of the year. About 24 hours after the vaccine my gut muscles started to react in severe pain.  Within an hour it as as bad as the accident then it elevated to a dull bit prominent stabling pain in my lower left abdomen area.  Not being completely unsure it wasn't my intestines, I drank some Miralax.  We were really close to a trip to the ER at this moment.  Instead of running laps between the toilet and bed I layed in bed continuously this time.  The pain subsided just a tad, but I was able to doze off for a few seconds at a time and it felt like a miracle. Three hours later I woke, nearly pain free but still very tender.  When I got up I could feel the tenderness a lot, but the pain had subsided.  When I went vertical  I could feel it getting worse again, although very slowly. I proceeded to spend the rest of the day and following day in bed.  I'm still tender but good. So I believe  the muscle scaring as severely agitated by the vaccine.

Details of symptoms with time of onset, duration and severity are provided below (Note: Injection with 2nd dose of Moderna vaccine took place at 9:24AM on 07APR21):  07APR21, 10:30AM ? Arm Pain: Onset of mild pain in arm that was noticed when not touching the arm; Level of pain was a ?1? out of 10).  An annoying level of pain where the pain ramped up to 3 or 4 on a scale of 10 when the arm was moved about began at 7:00PM on 07APR21 and lasted 12 hours until 7:00AM on 08APR21.  The pain diminished to a mild ache for another 33 hours until it became insignificant by 4:00PM on 09APR21.  07APR21, 1:00PM ? Dry Eyes: Onset of an intermittent feeling of very dry eyes that lasted approximately 1-2 hours at a time and continued over a period of 9 hours until 10PM on 07APR21.  07APR21, 3:30PM - Fatigue: Onset of mild fatigue that steadily increased until bedtime at 10:00PM on 07APR21; and was significantly more pronounced at 1:00AM on 08APR21 (was difficult to stand and walk 20? to closet to obtain a thermometer; could not walk straight and bumped into hallway on left 4-5 times). Joint Pain and Muscle Aches: Onset of joint pain and muscle aches that occasionally became annoying with twinges of pain. These symptoms subsided by 7:30AM on 09Apr21.  07APR21, 7:15PM ? Dizziness: Onset of mild dizziness that lasted 12 hours until 7:15AM on 08APR21.  08APR21, 1:00AM ? Measured Fever: Decided to measure temperature due to significant chills and shivering and found temperature was 101.0 at 1:00AM on 08APR21.  At 3:00PM on 08APR21, my temperature was 100.2 (this was 4.5 hours after taking one extended release tablet of 650mg acetaminophen).  At 3:00AM on 09APR21, my temperature measured 98.6 degrees and has remained near there ever since.  09APR21, 4:00PM ? On 4/8 the expected flu like symptoms began. On 4/9 around 10am my back and chest hurt. Around 12pm on 4/8 I had severe nerve like pain in my neck, back, chest that was radiating throughout my arms and body. I went to the ER they did an EKG, X-ray, blood test, contrasted CT scan to rule out blood clots. My blood pressure and pulse and respiratory were all high. I was given morphine, toradol and a steroid through IV to control the pain. The pain caused me to feel immobile due to the more I moved the more it hurt. I was discharged after no life threatening issues were found even still with an elevated bp and pulse. The doctor did say he was concerned of the pain radiating but was unable to state from what. I was sent home with morphine pills (which I have no taken any as we are in a large opioid pandemic as well and I am a clinical therapist). I could not sleep when I returned home. I had to sit straight up. I took Tylenol and it relieved the pain slightly. On 4/10 I attempted a car ride to get out of the house. Shortly after leaving my house my face became bright red, I couldn?t breathe well, I felt extremely hot and the pain was no radiating down my legs. I went to the pharmacy that gave me the shot as they have a clinic. My bp was 147/97 with a pulse of 116 and a fever now of 101.4 ( I havent had the fever until this point). They advised me to go back to the ER. Upon arriving to the ER for the second time in two days. Same test were given besides the CT.  I was given toradol by IV and saline again. The pain continues to radiate though my body. I can barely move. Again it is not muscle pain but nerve pain! I can barely move my neck or legs. The hospital discharged me again as administer a Covid test. The rapid was negative. These are symptoms from the shot there is  no coincidence. My wbc was 7.2 on 4/9 but 17.1 on 4/10
LAB_DATA: Chest X-ray, contrast CT scan, metabolic blood test, EKG were given on 4-9. Chest X-ray, metabolic blood test, EKG were given on 4/10

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Had no side effects whatsoever for many hours. Felt completely fine until about 7:30 pm, while I was making my plate of dinner. Felt lightheaded, dizzy, and hot. I began to black out, so I sat down, which helped for a few moments to subside lightheadedness. I was still feeling hot, so I walked a few feet to my back door and sat down on the steps outside to cool off. Within minutes, my vision blurred completely, I saw stars, and completely blacked out. My mother, who was nearby, heard me fall on the steps. She said my eyes rolled back, my body was completely limp, I was not breathing but rather making gurgling noises from my throat. She propped my head up, which allowed me to breathe properly, and I came to.   If my mother had not been nearby, I am convinced I would be dead right now. I saw the light, saw the other side, saw my relatives. I have had a near death experience once before, and this was exactly like that.

On Sunday April 4th, her behavior intensified into delusions and hallucinations.  She was talking to people not there and making bizarre statements.  She was taken to emergency hospital late Sunday night and given a blood and urine test and sent home.  By Monday morning, she had not slept the entire night and was shouting out, trying to leave the house and her hallucinations and delusions had intensified.  We took her to Emergency room, where she was diagnosed with psychotic behavior and was admitted to the psychiatric ward.  She is expected to be released today, April 11th, 2021.
LAB_DATA: Given a Urine Test and Blood Test on Sunday, April 4th.  Urine test for UTI was inconclusive and blood test was normal Given a Urine Test and Blood Test on Monday, April 5th, as well as a CT scan.  Urine test for UTI continued to be inconclusive, blood test was normal and CT was scan was normal. Patient was placed on anti-psychotic medication while in the psychiatric ward.  After about three days of non-sleep, she finally began to sleep.  She is doing well under the medication but is very sedated.
OTHER_MEDS: No Prescription drugs Takes alavert on occasion for allergies Tums
HISTORY: Patient is cognitively disabled, but functions fairly well with day to day activities and routines.  She has not experienced any incidents or conditions that she displayed beginning on March 31st 2021.

On March 10 (the day after my vaccine) I felt the normal body aches and had a pretty bad headache. That all went away in the evening on March 10. Since that day I have had off and on dizziness/lightheadedness. On March 19 I fainted in my kitchen. I hit my kitchen table and had a huge knot on my head and bruises all down my left side of my body. My left shoulder still hurts from the fall and I still have a small knot on my head (left side just above my left eye on my forehead). I went to my primary care doctor on  March 24 and reported the event. I asked if it could be related to the COVID vaccine and she said she wasn't sure since the Jansen one was so new, but that she had seen these effects from the other two vaccines.  At the doctor's office my blood pressure was on the lower end (110/60). My normal blood pressure runs about 118/70. They ran some blood work and that all came back normal. They did an EKG in the office, but my blood pressure stayed pretty close to the same as it was the first reading. They then sent me to get a CT scan on my head, which also came back normal. She did diagnose me with a concussion. I was out of work the entire week (March 22-March 26) due to this. She also ordered me to have an echo done. While at the office for the echo, my blood pressure ran 99/46 (this was on March 31). The results of the echo came back normal.  I also got a monitor to wear for 72 hours on March 31. I took that to the doctor on April 5 and I am still waiting on results from that.  Since the event on March 19, I have had headaches and body aches. I have also had slight lightheadedness off and on.
OTHER_MEDS: Natazia (birth control) - take one a day

I was advised by the Anticoagulation Clinic to enroll through the VAERS System in regards to my adverse reaction to the J&J Vaccine and the Deep Vein Thrombosis (DVT),

Developed acute-onset, sharp right pelvic/groin pain radiating to right groin and flank the day after receiving first Pfizer COVID vaccine.   Non-contrast CT abd/pelv revealed right ovarian cyst which resolved on follow-up vaginal ultrasound 1 week later.  Within about 2 days, the sharp pain progressed to burning neuropathic-type pain across the pelvic/pubic region and down bilateral inner thighs to knee level.  Pain was constant.  After 10-14 days, the pain transitioned from burning sensation to sensation of feeling cold (both on skin and deep tissues) that would feel normal to the touch.  It is symmetric on both sides and begins at the level of umbilicus and involves both groins and medial thighs. Symptoms worsen with sitting or standing up for prolonged periods of time (and become more noticeable/bothersome) and as the day progresses.  About 2 weeks later, the severe burning pain progressed to include bilateral buttocks and outer thighs as well.  MRI brain/cervical/thoracic/lumbar spine largely normal (tarlov cysts S2-S3, small left disc protrusion C5-C6).  CBC, BMP, TSH, B12, B6, lyme titer, ESR normal.  Currently being treated with gabapentin 300mg TID.
LAB_DATA: 1/12/21: CBC, BMP, pregnancy test, UA all normal MRI lumbar spine 1/19/21 - incidental tarlov cyst S2-S3, otherwise normal 1/28/21: TSH, ESR, lyme, B12 - normal MRI brain/cervical/thoracic 1/29/21 - small left disc protrusion C5-C6, otherwise normal 2/15/21: glucose, Vit B6 - normal

weakened connective tissue / mixed connective tissue disease; hearing loss; vision loss; neurogenic bladder; intractable vertigo; double vision; visual floaters; unsteady when she stood / balance difficulties; anxiety; panic attacks; sleep apnea; depression; atypical response to antidepressants; numbness and tingling in her lower extremities; cognitive difficulties; numbness and tingling in her lower extremities; involuntary movements; tics; hypoxia; vaginismus; endometriosis; sinus tachycardia; chronic joint pain / sleep disturbances / chronic fatigue syndrome (CFS); complex regional pain syndrome (CRPS) / pain in nerves / burning nerve pain of the CRPS; sinus tachycardia; pediatric acute-onset neuropsychiatric syndrome (PANS); pelvic floor dysfunction; daily seizures / convulsions; Autoimmune Disease; Trouble walking the halls; pain in her bones, nerves; mother did not consent to daughter receiving a third shot of Gardasil; dizziness and shakiness, headache, and nausea/ increased heartbeat and felt faint and unsteady when she stood/ Postural Orthostatic Tachycardia Syndrome (POTS)/ dysautonomia; This initial spontaneous report was received from a lawyer and patient's mother regarding a case in litigation and refers to a 15-year-old female patient. Information on the patient's concurrent conditions, medical history or concomitant therapy was not reported.      On 02-OCT-2013, the patient received her first shot of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) (lot#, expiration date, dose, route of administration and anatomical location were not reported). On 03-DEC-2013, the patient received her second shot of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) (lot#, expiration date, dose, route of administration and anatomical location were not reported). It was claimed that as a result of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL), the patient sustained autoimmune disease, including postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome (POTS), dysautonomia and other serious injuries. It was reported that quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) and its ingredients caused patient's autoimmune disease and other related injuries and had resulted in her suffering from severe, debilitating, disabling and painful chronic injuries. Prior to receiving her quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) injections, patient was doing well and maintaining overall good health. She had no autoimmune diseases, and no autonomic issues and no orthostasis.   Within one week following her second quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) injection, patient began experiencing dizziness and shakiness, headache, and nausea. She also noticed an increased heartbeat and felt faint and unsteady when she stood. Considering these post-quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) symptoms, and her rapidly declining health, patient's mother did not consent to patient receiving a third shot of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL).  As the months progressed, so did patient's injuries. She was seen by multiple physicians and specialists for her complaints which included: daily seizures; intractable vertigo and nausea exacerbated by double vision; visual floaters; balance difficulties; fatigue; anxiety and panic attacks; convulsions; sleep apnea and sleep disturbances; depression and atypical response to antidepressants; cognitive difficulties; numbness and tingling in her lower extremities; involuntary movements and tics; weakened connective tissue and chronic joint pain; vision and hearing loss; vaginismus and endometriosis.  As a result of her post-quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) symptoms, patient was unable to engage in normal activities that a teenager would enjoy. She no longer could participate in school and choir events in the same manner she used to prior to her quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) injections, her physical activities declined, she was constantly tired, dizzy, fatigued or in pain. Patient's vision and cognitive abilities declined, she was taken out of school had to complete the majority of her high school classes via homebound and one-on-one tutoring. Patient could no longer physically attend school in a normal fashion due to her deteriorated medical condition.  Studies, including serum samples from June 2018, demonstrated that patient tested positive for the anti-alpha-1 adrenergic antibodies, anti-beta-2 adrenergic antibodies, anti-muscarinic cholinergic receptor 1 antibodies, anti-muscarinic cholinergic receptor 3 antibodies, and anti-muscarinic cholinergic receptor 4 antibodies. Patient is at risk for anti-AT1R antibodies and anti-ETAR antibodies.  Based upon her chronic and severe post-quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) symptoms and adverse events as outlined above and the tests performed by her medical providers, patient had been diagnosed with various medical conditions, including but not limited to, POTS, sinus tachycardia, chronic fatigue syndrome (CFS), mixed connective tissue disease, complex regional pain syndrome (CRPS), pediatric acute-onset neuropsychiatric syndrome (PANS), pelvic floor dysfunction, endometriosis, vaginismus, neurogenic bladder, worsened hearing loss, progressive vision loss in both central acuity and peripheral vision, seizures and sleep apnea.  Patient contends that her quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) injections caused her to develop serious and debilitating injuries, including but not limited to autonomic, neurological, heterogenous autoimmune disease, POTS, as well as a constellation of adverse symptoms, complications, injuries, and other adverse events, many of which are alleged herein and all of which were caused by quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL) or otherwise linked to her quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL)-induced autoimmune disorder.  As a proximate result of Company's wrongful acts and omissions and its negligent and fraudulent testing, labeling, manufacturing, marketing and promotion of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL), patient had suffered and continues to suffer severe and permanent physical injuries and associated symptomology and has suffered severe and permanent emotional injuries, including pain and suffering. Patient also had a substantial fear of suffering additional and ongoing harms, including but not limited to now being at an increased risk of cancer and future symptoms and harms associated with her autoimmune disease and other injuries caused by quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL). As a direct and proximate result of her quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL)-induced injuries, patient had suffered and continues to suffer economic losses, including considerable financial expenses for medical care and treatment, and diminished income capacity, and she will continue to incur these losses and expenses in the future.  The outcome of all events was not recovered/not resolved. The reporter considered all events to be disabling and related to quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL).  Information regarding this patient was also received via 02-APR-2021. Additional information was reported: as a result of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL), the patient also experienced hypoxia, trouble walking and pain in bones, nerves, and joints. Her physical activities were drastically limited. It was reported that before Covid-19 pandemic, patient was able to alleviate some of her pain with ketamine infusions, which gave her relief from the burning nerve pain of the CRPS. She was not able to receive the treatment in nearly a year due to the pandemic, and the pain in her bones, nerves, and joints was constant.  The outcome of the events was resported as not recovered/not resolved. The events were considered to be related to quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine(GARDASIL).  Upon internal review, the events of POTS, mixed connective tissue disease, hearing loss, vision loss, neurogenic bladder, seziures/convulsions, hypoxia and autoimmune disease were considered to be medically significant.

The patient's medical history included fibromyalgia, ulcerative colitis, and obesity. Concomitant product use included:levothyroxine 150 mg, verapamil 120 mg (blood pressure), losartan 100 mg (blood pressure), Asacol 800 mg three  times a day, Eliquis 5 mg, alprazolam (Xanax) 0.5 mg up to three a day, Centrum silver once a day, iron pill once a day, B12 500 mcg once a day, GNC probiotic 50 billion CFU, vitamin D 1000 mg, Citracal max Plus D3 once a day, magnesium glycinate, diphenydrinate.   On 15-FEB-2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number015M20A.).  On 16Mar2021,approximately 1 day prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their first/second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: 001B21A.) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 17Mar2021 about 10 am, the patient woke up screaming with pain coming from around the liver area radiating under the right and left breasts. The patient states that taking deep breaths lead to excessive vomiting resulting in the ultimate loss of 10lbs. After the initial episode of vomiting, there was only nausea. An ambulance transported her to the hospital, as she continued to scream, resulting in being medicated to calm her down. The medication used is unknown. In the hospital, received morphine for three days In the hospital, she was told her temperature reached 101F. Upon returning home on 19Mar2021 afternoon, her temperature ranged from 99.4 to 99.8, one day peaking 101F. Today (29Mar2021) it is back to a more normal temperature: 98F.  In the hospital, ultrasounds, CAT scan, and blood and urine tests was performed, results were not provided. Patient reports currently she is still in pain, that has reduced from a 10 to a 2. About four hours later, I realized I was scratching my stomach and chest while watching TV. Upon raising my shirt, I saw a bright red rash on the top part of my belly that extended underneath both breasts and to the area directly over my heart, and up my left side into my left armpit. All of these areas were very itchy. I put Hydrocortisone cream on them, which helped reduce the itching quite quickly. I then took half a Benadryl tablet. When I awoke the next morning, the areas that had been bright red now had dark red dots but did not itch. However, I had lines of a bright red, itchy rash on both thighs near my groin. I again applied Hydrocortisone cream and took Benadryl, which helped abate the symptoms. Lymph nodes in my left armpit were quite sore as well, so I took ibuprofen.
