I  administered the Janssen Covid-19  Vaccine using  a syringe/needle supplied by Janssen with the Covid-19 vaccine shipment.  Upon removing the syringe from patient's arm, the needle and it's yellow/orange safety cover became detached from the syringe and remained partially in the patient's arm and partially sticking out of his arm. I used a gloved hand and grasped the safety cover at the rim and pulled it in a manner that allowed the needle to come straight out.   It appeared to me that he had received the full dose of the vaccine (the plunger had been fully depressed before I attempted to remove the syringe/needle and the syringe did not contain any remaining vaccine in the barrel.  Patient did not  do anything that indicated he was aware of what happened, but I told him about it, showed him the needle and the syringe and told him that the full dose had been administered before this happened. Patient said he thought he felt a small splash of liquid on his arm, and possibly also on his forearm.  I called Janssen Pharmaceuticals and spoke to Pharmacist. She said if the patient received at least 50% of the dose then no further action is required. If he received less than 50% of the dose then a full dose should be administered in the alternate arm.  Janssen reference #020954274.  I relayed this info in patient, he said he agreed that he received at least 50% of the dose.  He was curious if there is a way to tell if he is fully protected against Covid-19.  I advised him to check with his doctor to see if any testing can be done to determine that.
CUR_ILL: no illnesses reported. screening questionnaire indicated patient did not feel sick.

In the middle of the night of the 10th of April I started having what seemed like normal side effects---muscle aches, headache, fatigue.. and then all day on the 10th the same side effects.   Then last night I slept 9 straight hours but woke up  sweating a couple times in night and in morning woke up sweating but my aches and headache seemed better than the day before so I went downstairs to make tea.  After pouring a glass of orange juice and having a couple sips I started to feel strange --dizzy and oversome with a strange feeling that was not quite like the feeling before fainting -- my back had a weird pain and i was a little nauseous as well. ..it was more overwhelming -- more loss of control like a huge wave of dizziness and ringing.  I made my way to a couch to try to regain balance -- but was still very dizzy-- something happened to make me try to get up and go upstairs so I remember walking 12 feet or so then told myself to sit down.  Before that happened I must have blacked out.  I faintly remember moving myself across the floor but then must have blacked out again.  I woke up at the base of the stairwell and then was able to walk upstairs.    I had collapsed the first time onto a hard floor as my orange juice glass had spilled all over and when I got upstairs my sweatshirt was covered in juice.  I don't remember any of that.  Once upstairs I drank water and have been fine since then.  I had eaten dinner the night before but maybe it was the sweating in the night that dehydrated me and i cramped up and had a strange pain in my back---i don't know.  I am a very healthy 56 yr old woman 5'3" 105 lbs so maybe the Johnson and JOhnson one dose was a lot for my body or maybe my body was just doing what it's supposed to do to react to vaccine.... i also may have had asymptomatic covid in the last year so my body was overreacting.   This happened 7 hours ago and I seem fine aside from slight headache and continued weakness from vaccine but I thought I should report the incident in case there might be something more or in case others had similiar responses.
OTHER_MEDS: I did take one ibuprofen the morning of vaccine not to prepare for vaccine but I had a slight headache

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After the first dose, I experienced only mild fatigue and a mild headache within a couple hours of the injection. Later within 10 hours, I developed strong injection site direness that affected my sleep but abated within 12 hours. Therefore, I was expecting more or less similar symptoms with the second dose. Instead, I felt absolutely nothing for nearly twelve hours until I fondly felt mild injection site soreness. I went to bed around 1 am. At around 2 am I awoke with such strong chills that they were almost like convulsions. I was sweating and had a headache.  More concerning though was the tachypnea and wheezing. I was wheezing as if I had asthma to the point that my lunch?s were whistling and I found it difficult to take sufficient breaths. This lasted 30 minutes to one hour before a sting enough that I fell asleep again, still with mild left arm soreness, sweating, mild fever, headache and wheezing. When I awoke a few hours later at around 8 am, I was so fatigued that I could not move. I had a mild headache still but the breathing was better without wheezing and now only hampered by frequent belching (passing off the CO2 buildup from the tachypnea most likely). However, I was so exhausted that I lay in bed for another four hours. When I forced myself up to shower and move, I had a sudden severe depressive attack of uncontrollable crying in the shower. I also had body aches throughout the morning. These symptoms are the same or similar to those felt when I had COVID, so I knew them and that they should pass, yet I did not expect them to be so strong  and the tachypnea with wheezing was initially very disconcerting until it began to ease.  By approximately 11 hours later,  all symptoms had passed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I experienced a low-grade fever (100), muscle and joint pain, pain at the injection site, and fatigue during the first 24 hours after receiving the vaccine. A little less than 24 hours after the vaccine, my fever broke, and I began to develop a rash on my legs, which consisted of small, itchy, bug-bite like red bumps. I consulted my primary care physician, who recommended I take Benadryl. The rash worsened and spread to my torso - stomach, chest, underarms, and forearms - but was never present at the injection site. The rash on my chest was significantly different than the rest of my body, and when I saw an urgent care provider (5 days after being vaccinated), she diagnosed the chest rash as a separate issue (Folliculitis) and prescribed oral antibiotics. I saw no improvement in any symptoms. A week after being vaccinated and symptoms not improving, I saw my Allergist, who prescribed a 10-day course of oral steroids (Prednisone). My symptoms gradually improved, but the rash did not fully disappear for approximately 3 weeks after the first symptoms appeared.

In the first week after the vaccine, the pain was quite sharp and severe in my left hip.  Over time the pain spread further down my leg and was a searing ache. About four days I awoke having what seemed like one of my sleep cycle panic attacks with the exception that I did not experience mental panic, only very rapid heart beat and high blood pressure and arm tingling.  I took alprazolam as prescribed by my physician.  The symptoms were very slow to abate.  I was concerned I was having a stroke or heart attack but decided it was just a panic attack.  By week four following my first vaccine the leg pain had lessened.  After the second vaccine, the entire scenario above reoccured including  hip and leg pain on my left side.  The pain in my joint was not as sharp but it is severe enough to wake me up.  It occurs at about 3:30 am at night and lasts 2-3 hours.  I had a second panic attack with the same description of symptoms (severe rapid heart beat (153) high blood pressure (can provide exact measure - I recall the upper number was 165 and I typically have normal blood pressure).  Took alpralozam and the cardiac synptoms were slow to abate and in fact resurged even after medication.  I continue to have left-side hip and knee join pain and leg pain in my sleep to this day on the same very regular, predictable schedule and the pain continues to be enough to wake me up and make me very uncomfortable, thereby disrupting my sleep every night.  I have had no further "panic" attacks.  At this time, my left side joint and leg pain is somewhat noticeable during the day but I do not have mobility issues.  Am able to walk, exercise etc. normally.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had severe abdominal pain that started about 1.5 hr after the 2nd dose of the vaccine.  I was doubled over in pain and I can tolerate alot of pain. Within 12 hours, I had developed diarrhea,  migraines and a significant facial rash, across my nose and cheeks, my malar rash, and across  my forehead. I had no itching, no throat swelling, no shortness of breath. I was in touch with both my GP and Rheumatologist. Because of the vaccine, we felt it cause a significant flare of my SLE, but opted to defer steroid treatment due to not being on them daily already. If I had more significant issues we would have likely started steroids. The diarrhea lasted for 2 weeks, but was more of an inconvenience issue. The face rash was uncomfortable and lasted about 10 days. I'm only sharing this for information sharing as it relates to my chronic immunosuppressive disease, Lupus.

Patient reports to pharmacist that he had not eaten anything yet for the day and does have a fear of needles as well as history of passing out when getting blood drawn. Pharmacist provided a bottle of water and a plain chocolate bar for the patient to consume while waiting for EMS to arrive. EMS checked over patient since he complained of pain at the base of skull as a result from fall in the bathroom. EMS checked blood pressure (138/74) and blood sugar (78) at 2:18pm. 1st Dose of Moderna Vaccine delivered Left Arm Intramuscular approx 8:30 am 4/8/21. Left arm pain began (normally as expected by described side effects) in afternoon, however this progressed to more severe pain in evening precluding normal arm movement and causing problems with sleeping. 24 hours later on 4/9/21, symptoms still persisted, and increased in intensity throughout the day. By evening of 4/9/21 (approx 36 hours after vaccine dose) arm pain was extreme with inability to lift or hold weight. Fever, lethargy, nausea set in. Sleeping was near impossible overnight due to extreme arm pain, which was sharp and took my breath away upon any movement and was throbbing even when immobile and non weight bearing. Fever seemed to break sometime at dawn and by 48 hours later, the arm severe arm pain symptoms started to subside with more normal arm pain and movement returning by afternoon of 4/10/21. I did not take any NSAID or other drugs before or during course of side effects. As this was my first dose of vaccine and I am not aware of having been Covid positive previously, the vaccine side effects after the first dose were very unexpected. I have never had any issues with other vaccinations in my life, nor do I have any known allergies. I am of good health with no underlying health conditions.

I received my 2nd Moderna vaccine dose on 5Feb2021 at 4pm.  I felt fine until about 10pm when I started experiencing the expected arm soreness, fever, myalgias, arthralgias, headaches, and chills.  By 1am on 6Feb2021 my fever went from 97.1 to 101.8.  My myalgias and arthralgias were extreme.  Despite ample hydration (3 L of oral rehydration formula from midnight until morning) my kidney output dropped to zero from 1am on 6Feb2021 to 2pm on 6Feb2021 (13 hours).  This started resolving around 2pm.  I did go to the ER around 3pm to have a Basic Metabolic Panel and CK checked.  These results were within normal limits.  The specific gravity on my urine analysis was obviously low due to my hydration of 3L of fluid.  By the time I was discharged from the ER my urine output was in overdrive and my vitals were stable.  My other symptoms resolved over the next 2 days except for fatigue. Was able to work the next week despite lingering low-level fatigue. A week later I went cross-country skiing using the same ski gear I have been using for the past 15 years.  My ski boots extend up to my mid-calves.  During the ski outing my lower legs became extremely sore.  Upon removing my boots at the end of the ski trip, I found that I was completely bruised on both my lower extremities.  This has NEVER happened before.  I went back to the ER for additional bloodwork.  This time a CBC, complete metabolic panel, INR, PT/PTT, CK, ESR, CRP were performed.  All results were within normal limits and I was discharged with stable vitals.  The bruising resolved over the following week.  The low-level fatigue remained. One month later I went skiing again.  This time my lower legs became very sore, but there was no bruising.  The low-level fatigue remained. I do have HSV and use valacyclovir only prn. Prior to the vaccine I would have rated my health as excellent.  I am now 2.5 months out and still do not feel 100% back to my pre-vaccine health.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Upon receiving 1st dose, pt ambulated to observation area w/ unsteady gait. Pt sat down in observation area w/ noticeable labored breathing, inspiratory stridor, cough, dyspnea.  Pt was pale and diaphoretic. Pt was offered vitals check by medical staff, pt refused, stating she recently had an AMI and this was normal for her. Pt stated she carried EpiPen due to latex and iodine allergies, and "if this was an allergic reaction," she "would have known by now." Pt was told to notify medical staff of symptom changes. Throughout her 15 minute wait, pt produced violent coughing and could be seen with noticeable SOB. Pt stood up and ambulated with unsteady gait for approximately 5 ft, where she stopped and was assisted into w/c. Pt was wheeled out to vehicle, where she was asked to stay for another 15 minutes given her symptoms, pt refused. Pt was offered vitals check, pt refused, stating she is "just a minute away from home" and if she would place herself "on low oxygen" upon arrival. Pt drove off, returning approximately two minutes later. Pt c/o throat swelling, SOB, w/ inspiratory stridor, hoarse voice, and violent cough. EMS was called at this time. EMS transported to local hospital.

Abnormal menses.  Huge clots.  Velocity and volume of blood extreme.  (Different from previous experiences of menorrhagia).  The only other time I experienced this type of dramatic and concerning bleeding was after I took the Hepatitis vaccine (first shot) about 2 years ago.  I think that's the only other vaccine I've had as an adult.  There is mention of heavy bleeding as a rare side effect for Hepatitis vaccine, and I surely hope you will study this effect from Covid vaccine as it took nearly a year to regulate my cycle after the Hepatitis vaccine reaction.  I've seen some reports suggesting that the excessive bleeding that women are experiencing after the Covid vaccine is due to stress and that is just plain insulting.  Stress does affect the menstrual cycle; that is well-known, but this is something entirely different.  I have also had small clots in the nose during the past several days, which again, is highly abnormal for me.  Thank you for looking into the bleeding side effects that hundreds (if not more) women are struggling with at this time.
PRIOR_VAX: hepatitis vaccine  Fall 2019

The following morning, I had to scramble out of bed at 6:30 AM to run to the bathroom before soaking my sheets with a monster, Stephen King Carrie-worthy period that has been relentless and continued non-stop for 2 weeks, unabated.  I was in contact immediately with my endocrinologist, fearing that my thyroid meds needed to be upped in dosage.  And I was scheduling an appt. with a new gyn as well (won't see this person till June as a new patient) but hey, prior to this, I had no period through much of 2020.  My endocrinologist put me on a daily dosage of medroxyprogesterone to halt the period.  A week later, as of yesterday, 4/10, I was still bleeding heavily.  Today, it is lighter so hopefully, it's coming to an end.   I'd assume my sore arm was the extent of the Moderna side effects but then  came across an article by fluke and happenstance this morning.
LAB_DATA: I have an appt. with my endocrinologist on 4/28 and now dread my 2nd Moderna shot, which is scheduled for 4/24.  I've emailed him a copy of the article.  It's so easy for women to go down into their burrows and suffer out anomalies with periods and think oh, it must be in my head or due to this, that or the other, my age, that I lost a little weight, that I have a history of being a woman, buck it up, shouldn't have eaten the Easter chocolate, etc. etc.  So it was eye-opening to see that article and read through all of the outpouring of others who are reporting The Period from  immediately after getting Moderna.
HISTORY: Losing pandemic weight, endometriosis but hey, my period stopped for much of 2020 as I'm in perimenopause.

We left before seeing my father in law to go home and use my nebulizer. For the moment, I used my inhaler, which doesn?t work as well. As I was driving away from vac site, I became increasingly disoriented and could not navigate a very easy route home which should take about 40minutes.  Suddenly unable to read freeway signs or judge distances, or speed on the freeway.  Light began to hurt my eyes, headache pounded & became extremely nauseous and tired.  Got off fwy, because I didn't feel safe, planned to take surface streets, but became so disoriented (on a route I know well) it took about 1 1/2 hours to get to a familiar location that should have taken 20 mins. K ept making wrong turns even when using maps.  Finally, had to call my husband to pick me up.  Couldn't make it home & I use this route often and have been for over 20 years.  Once home, extremely tired for about 3 days.    As the weeks went by my disorientation did not completely go back to normal.  I still am impaired (compared to my normal functioning).  Unable to juggle a few items in my head as I normally do.  My brain feels foggy & I am having memory issues with things that are routine.  When I went to have my hair colored on 2/26/21 my hair looked the same as always afterward, but when I returned 4/1/21, I had lost about 1/3 of my hair -- it began falling out each time I brushed it or washed. It seems to have stopped falling out for now.

I wasn't sure how to indicate which dose I'm reporting on.  It's my second dose of a vaccine but my first of Johnson & Johnson.  My first shot for Covid-19 was a Moderna shot, to which I had a bad reaction (immediate and prolonged lightheadedness reported already on this site).  My doctor advised me that my second dose should be a Johnson & Johnson vaccine, as per information he had received from the CDC.  So, 28 days after the first shot I had the Johnson & Johnson vaccine.  I experienced the expected side effects of body aches, chills, headache--no big deal on day 2, but on day 3, I started some lightheadedness, as did my daughter who had the shot the same day.  Her lightheaded subsided the next day, but mine continued into day 4 and got worse when it became accompanied by pressure in my head/ears, and it felt like I was talking in a tunnel with echoing.  I couldn't function the rest of the day.  Today, the head pressure is not there, but the lightheadedness and shakiness are still there.  I hope I fully recover from these shots, but I don't have a lot of hope.
LAB_DATA: No testing so far, but if this doesn't go away pretty soon, I will need to check into it.
OTHER_MEDS: Standard strength multivitamin Tums 750 mg. 3 times a day Vit. D3, 2000 IU/day Metamucil - 1 T. per day

Not a terrible adverse reaction (for me) but just reporting in case the info is of use.   Swelling of hands and redness in hands and very itchy skin all over - this started about 4.5 hours after receiving the vaccination.  I immediately took 50mg Benadryl and 2x my normal cromolyn dose as soon as swelling started in my hands and itchiness was noticeable. Within 30 min the swelling came down. I did NOT feel my throat swelling or closing. My breathing was slightly more labored, so I also took a dose of prescribed inhaler about 5 hours after vaccination. Next few nights after vaccination I had a lot of itchy skin and burning skin sensations, all managed with extra doses of Benadryl.  I plan to get the second dose, but just wanted to report as I have no idea what types of adverse reactions y'all are looking for. I have no idea if my reaction would or would not have escalated further to needing an epic-pen use/urgent care trip had I not taken Benadryl and cromolyn promptly.   *(I had pre medicated with some Benadryl before vaccine at 9am if that is useful info)  Thanks for your time and for all y'all are doing to keep us all safe.

I sat down to try to maintain a sense of calm - but got off the subway after a few stops and met with a friend whom I had texted, to take care of me. From the point on, I was very shaken and agitated, and have been since the event.    I have never experienced anxiety, depression, or any such symptoms in my life before, nor was I nervous or anxious about having received the vaccine. I went to Urgent Care Sunday morning, April 11th, the morning after the event. My resting pulse was 97 BPM (normally 52-54) - and my blood pressure much higher than normal - 175/110. The doctor insisted I go home "and relax".    I still feel uneasy and shaken from the event.

But what I didn't expect was from then until now which has been approximately 6 weeks I am cramped and my lower abdomen everyday and I'm also experiencing atrial fibrillation almost constantly which I've never done before. All my episodes with a fib in the past were due to times when I had been very nauseous or very cramped and would go into a fib which lasted 10 12 hours but for the last 12 years I've been on atenolol for that and it has kept me from experiencing those problems. But since the second shot I'm experiencing atrial fibrillation like I said every day with the cramping which I've never had before to that extent. I'm reporting this because something isn't quite right and if this is a coincidence it's a pretty good one. Thank you for reading this and if I can be of any further help please feel free to contact me through my email.

She began having a tonic-clonic seizure at 1:15 pm lasting around 90 seconds. Patient was post-ictal for approximately 1-2 minutes. When EMS and Clinical Leads were notified, patient was not actively seizing. Patient was not responsive to verbal stimuli while post-ictal. After ~3min pt was able to respond and follow verbal and tactile commands. Pt was c/o feeling tired / nauseous. Pt was AOx3 and able to follow commands.  Patient was assessed by EMS and clin leads, she was placed on a stretcher, attached to monitor, vitals and BGM taken, 18g IV started on right hand and 20g IV access point attained on left hand. 15L NRB O2, 250mL NS bolus, 1L NS bolus   Pt remained stable and transport was called, pt was transferred to hospital for further evaluation/workup. SYMPTOM_TEXT: First shot: 7 hours after my first dose I experienced low fever 100.2 that last 2 days as well as chills. Severe pain in my left arm that subsided in about 24 hours. In addition , the first 48 hours I couldn't sleep. Slept 3 hours those nights despite feeling extremely tired. Brain fog and severe fatigue persisted for a full 7 days after the first shot.   Second shot: 12 hours after my second dose, around 10 pm that night sudden onset of fever, this time higher, rose to 101. Severe chills, nausea, diarrhea. These severe, flu-like symptoms lasted a little over 24 hours and then improved significantly. However, the stomach pains continued and the next morning (so about 24 hours after the second shot), I had heavy vaginal bleeding and cramping. This happened 21 days into my cycle and is highly abnormal for me. My cycle is regular and runs between 28 and 31 days, usually on the longer side. I track my periods, in the last 3 years it's never been 21 days and I've never had sudden onset of heavy bleeding like this, it always starts lighter and intensifies. Heavy bleeding continues as I'm writing this report. This is much heavier than usual for the full 6 days so far and seems to be getting heavier, not lighter as I would expect it to by day 6/7 certainly.

A little after 12pm, he complained of difficulty breathing and possibly not getting enough oxygen so I grabbed my equipment (since I'm a CNA) and checked his vitals. His B/P was very high ( 166/107), no fever (96.7), pulse was normal 72, and low respiration but oxygen was above 90. He said he needed to use the bathroom, I suggested using his urinal but he said he needed to have a bowel movement. Once he was in the bathroom, I went downstairs for a glass of water and then suddenly I heard a huge thump. I ran upstairs, knocked on the bathroom-no response but I could hear noises, so I opened the door and I saw he was face down on the floor, head under the bathroom sink counter, blood everywhere, and he was convulsing. I grabbed him immediately and moved him to his side (I had my fitbit on, it said it was 12:30pm), and he kept seizing. He looked discolored almost blueish color. I held him on his side, he vomited, making noises, but unable to speak, continuing to have a seizure. Seizure lasted three minutes. At 12:33pm, once he had calmed, I ran downstairs to find my phone. I was back at his side calling 911 at 12:35. Paramedics arrived 9 minutes later and took him to the hospital. My brother picked me up and took me to the hospital. Once outside his door, I noticed he was finishing taking X-Rays when he suddenly had another seizure.
LAB_DATA: Lab results came back fine (April 10, 2021 at 18:08), Head CT came back normal--no acute abnormality, no brain bleed, no mass (April 10 at 18:06). We did find out he had a left humerus fracture and multiple compressed discs. The next day, with more MRI, CT Scans, we found out he did have a dislocated left shoulder and since they'd need to go in surgically to fix it they would also go ahead with fixing his fractured humerus by putting in plate and screws. Surgery was set up for 2pm. He also had an EEG done before he could have surgery and it too looked fine. He has never suffered a seizure.
OTHER_MEDS: Over the counter REDD Remedies Gouch Liquid Formula

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 5 hours after I received the vaccine, I started to feel extremely fatigued and experienced some muscle aches. I took an Aleve and laid down for an hour long nap. At approximately 7:00pm, I woke up with more extreme muscle pain. By 8:00pm, my muscles were so tight and painful that it hurt to move, lay still, or go to the bathroom. It felt as though all of the muscles in the back of my body (from my back to my butt and legs) were spasming, Over the next few hours, my temperature rose to 102.7 and my heart rate spiked to 140-150 bpm. I also experienced chills and a headache. We sought the advice of a 24-hour nurse, who let us know these symptoms were likely normal side effects. I went to bed around 12:00am, and my temperature had dropped to 99.9 around 3:00am when I woke up to check it.  My heart rate eventually dropped below 100 bpm around 8:00am. I woke up around 10:00am on Saturday feeling much better than the day before. My temperature was around 99.1 when I woke up, and my symptoms included mild muscle aches, a moderate headache, and moderate fatigue. I continued to feel better throughout the day, with the headache gradually subsiding and a minor sore throat toward the end of the day. On Sunday, I felt back to normal, other than experiencing some mild-moderate fatigue.
OTHER_MEDS: Zyrtec, multivitamin, Fluoxetine (20 mg/day), Amitriptyline Hcl (10/mg)
CUR_ILL: I have been fighting tension headaches, so my doctor prescribed Amitriptyline before bed daily.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, Zomig  I had an anaphylactic reaction after taking Zomig and an antibiotic when I was a teenager. It is unclear whether I am allergic to the migraine medications, or if it was a drug interaction between the two prescribed medications.

To this day (one month later) by ability to recall memories and recall words remains poor. I have troubles forming sentences because words don't come to me. To this day I cannot recall anything that happened days 1-3 after the vaccine. I was able to write this report because my partner made me take notes on how I felt. Prior to the vaccine I never had an issue with memory recall. My physical reactions cleared during the second week after the vaccine. However, the mental reactions still stubbornly persist.

It was an awful, scary feeling and it come on in just two or three minutes after shot.

But since getting the vaccine, my period has lasted for 14 days with no signs of stopping.  On day 13, for a few hours I bled so heavily that I went to urgent care.  Since it was Saturday night and they're a small clinic, they couldn't conduct any real lab tests and I must wait till Monday to see my obgyn.  Prior to getting the vaccine, I NEVER had this much excess bleeding, and I never bled longer than 7 days (now it's been 14 days and counting) I am alarmed that the vaccine has clearly affected the length and intensity of my menstrual cycle, and no doctor seems to know why.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I felt fine all day and went to bed at 9:30pm. I woke up to my body shaking uncontrollably and I was freezing at 10:30pm. My wife felt my skin and she said I was burning up. Unfortunately our thermometer wasn't working so I don't know my temperature, but I have never in my life shaken so badly with a fever. I couldn't control myself and I was shaking so hard that my muscles were sore from it, but I still couldn't stop. I then began vomiting every 45 minutes or so. This happened for nearly 4 hours until 2:18am. Then very suddenly everything just stopped. No more feeling cold (actually I then felt very warm and couldn't cool off. I was sweating quite a bit). No more shaking. No more vomiting. I did get a wicked headache, but I figured it was due to dehydration and took two Advil. The Advil didn't do anything and I was awake until 5:59am because my head hurt too badly to sleep. Finally I slept for about 4.5 hours. Then I just felt worn out for most of the day on the 10th, and couldn't shake the headache. Then on the evening if the 10th, I started getting a sore throat and a slightly runny nose. I went to bed that way. When I woke up on the 11th (today) I still had the sore throat and slight runny nose. The headache was gone, but I felt tightness in my chest. As I went throughout the day, I've noticed that I'm short of breath with doing most things. I have two young children, so even taking care of them I feel like at times I'm struggling for breath. I'm not in bad shape and am a runner, so my cardio isn't bad. So I was surprised by this.
ALLERGIES: Hydrocodone. Poison Ivy. Silly string (I don't know what is in silly string that I'm allergic to.)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: DURING COVID VACCINATION CLINIC, DIVISION 1 EMPLOYEE ASSISTING WITH POST-VACCINE OBSERVATION REPORTED TO PHARMACIST THAT A PATIENT WAS FEELING LIGHTHEADED. SHE IDENTIFIED PATIENT WHO WAS DISTRESSED AND APPEARED UNSTEADY. THE PATIENT REPORTED THAT THEY HAD TUNNEL VISION AND FELT VERY LIGHTHEADED. PHARMACIST ASKED THE PATIENT TO REMAIN SEATED AND TRY TO TAKE SEVERAL DEEP BREATHS WHILE THE PHARMACIST HELD THE PATIENT'S LEFT SHOULDER TO ENSURE HE WOULD NOT FALL IF SYNCOPE OCCURRED. THE PATIENT HAD FLUTTERING EYELIDS AND APPEARED IAPHORETIC AT FIRST, BUT AFTER SEVERAL MINUTES RECOVERED SOMEWHAT. THE PATIENT REPORTED THAT HE HAD RARELY HAD SIMILAR EPISODES IN THE PAST DURING SOME MEDICAL PROCEDURES, BUT NEVER ASSOCIATED WITH A VACCINATION. PHARMACY TECHNICIAN HAD A D1 EMPLOYEE RADIO FOR A CODE WHITE AS SHE CONTACTED 911 ON HER CELLULAR PHONE. PARAMEDICS ARRIVED AND ASSESSED THE PATIENT'S HEART RATE, SEATED BLOOD PRESSURE. AND STANDING BLOOD PRESSURE. THE PATIENT REPORTED FEELING SLIGHTLY LIGHTHEADED WHEN FIRST STANDING, BUT MUCH IMPROVED OVERALL. THE PARAMEDICS INDICATED THAT THERE DID NOT SEEM TO BE A MEDICAL EMERGENCY BY THIS POINT AND EXPRESSED CONCERN THAT THE PATIENT MAY BE DEHYDRATED BUT THE PATIENT REFUTED THIS POSSIBILITY. HE ALSO STATED THAT HE HAD NOT RECENTLY OVEREXERTED HIMSELF AND HAD EATEN LUNCH EARLIER THAT AFTERNOON. PHARMACIST PROVIDED THE PATIENT WITH GATORADE AND ICE TO IMPROVE BLOOD SUGAR, ELECTROLYTE, AND HYDRATION STATUS AND THE PARAMEDICS DEPARTED. THE PATIENT REMAINED FOR APPROXIMATELY 30 MINUTES UNTIL HE WAS FEELING CLOSE TO BASELINE AND FELT COMFORTABLE LEAVING.
LAB_DATA: BLOOD PRESSURE AND HEART RATE BOTH SITTING AND STANDING WERE OBSERVED BY PARAMEDICS ON THE SCENE, AND ASSESSED TO BE NORMAL.

No adverse event occurred. The Janssen COVID-19 vaccine was inadvertently administered to a sixteen year old. The owner of a small local masonry company had arranged for and helped schedule COVID vaccines for his employees, which included  two of his children. We had originally discussed using the Pfizer vaccine for which his daughter was old enough. The day they were scheduled to receive the vaccine, we received our first shipment of Janssen vaccine. The company owner thought that would be a better choice for his employees due to it being a one dose vaccine. The masonry business is being to pick up rapidly now that it is warming up and concrete projects are starting and it would be difficult for them to return in 3 weeks for a second dose. The group decided to go with the Janssen vaccine .They arrived as a group in the evening and were processed for vaccination. We had been doing Pfizer vaccine all day and the minimum birthdate for vaccination was set to 4/9/2005, or 16 years old. We had just begun to do an evening of Janssen vaccine at 5:00pm and did not change the date to 4/9/2003, or 18 years old. This was the first time we had Janssen vaccine in our pharmacy. Patient was inadvertently vaccinated with the Janssen vaccine along with the rest of the group. The administration error was discovered later during the claim billing process.

This pain lasted 2 weeks, and was severe enough to prevent patient from sitting or standing for more than a few minutes at a time, especially during the first week of pain. Painkillers (Acetaminophen or NSAIDs) or muscle relaxants (cyclobenzaprine) did not help alleviate the pain. The pain started on March 17, and finally eased up on April 2 (the vaccination was on March 13). There is still some pain and stiffness in the left arm (currently in the biceps), but it is no longer severe. I began feeling soreness at the injection site started within 12 hours of receiving the vax.  The soreness progressively became worse over the next 7-9 days and was accompanied by swelling of the muscle around the injection site (peaking at about 7 days post-injection). The discomfort at times extended down my arm, but never past my elbow.  When extending my arm outwards (e.g., when reaching for something), I would feel an unusual stiffness and moderate discomfort in my arm.  As of April 12 (13 days post-vax), the swelling is largely gone, but there is still some discomfort when extending my arm outwards.  In addition, there appear to be dry patches of skin between the injection site and my armpit.  I have not sought medical treatment for these adverse reactions to date, nor do I anticipate needing to unless the discomfort becomes more intense.

Suspected vaccination failure; Haemophilus influenzae type B (Hib) Bacterimia; fever; This case was reported in a literature article and described the occurrence of suspected vaccination failure in a 8-month-old patient who received Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine for prophylaxis.   Co-suspect products included Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine (batch number UNK, expiry date unknown) for prophylaxis and Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine (batch number UNK, expiry date unknown) for prophylaxis.   The subject's past medical history included premature baby (born at 33-week). Concomitant products included PNEUMOCOCCAL CONJUGATE VACCINE.   On an unknown date, the patient received the 1st dose of Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine, the 2nd dose of Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine and the 3rd dose of Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine. On an unknown date, less than 9 months after receiving Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine, Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine and Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine, the patient experienced vaccination failure (serious criteria hospitalization and GSK medically significant), hemophilus bacteremia (serious criteria hospitalization and GSK medically significant) and fever (serious criteria hospitalization). On an unknown date, the outcome of the vaccination failure, hemophilus bacteremia and fever were unknown.   The reporter considered the vaccination failure, hemophilus bacteremia and fever to be related to Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine, Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine and Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccine.  Additional details were provided as follows: This case was reported in a literature article and described suspected vaccination failure, in a patient aged 8-month-old of unspecified gender, who was vaccinated with, who was vaccinated with Unspecified Haemophilus influenzae type B (Hib) vaccine (manufacturer unknown) for prophylaxis.   The patient was a part of retrospective cohort study that aimed to determine the association between bacteremia and vaccination status in children presenting to a pediatric emergency department. The study included children aged 2-36 months with blood cultures obtained in the pediatric emergency department between 1st January 2013 and 31st December 2017. The exposure of interest was immunization status, defined as number of Haemophilus influenzae type B (Hib) and Streptococcus pneumoniae vaccinations, and the main outcome positive blood culture. [In this study, Children aged 2-36 months with blood cultures obtained in the ED were eligible for inclusion. 2 months was chosen as the lower age limit due to an institutional febrile neonate guideline addressing the care of infants up to 60 days of life and 36 months as our upper age limit to maintain consistency with previous fever without source studies]. The patient was a 33-week premature baby. The patient did not have any high-risk medical condition which could increase the risk of bacteremia. No information on patient medical or family history or concurrent condition or concomitant medication was reported.   On an unknown date, the patient received 3 sets of Unspecified Hib vaccine (administration site or route unspecified, dose not reported, batch number not provided) and unspecified Pneumococcal vaccine. The age at vaccination was not reported. [In this study, children older than 7 months of age were considered under vaccinated if they had received fewer than 3 sets of vaccines. Patients were grouped according to the number of PCV and Hib vaccinations received].  On an unknown date between 1st January 2013 and 31st December 2017, an unknown period after vaccination, the patient experienced fever. The patient presented to pediatric emergency department and blood culture was obtained.  The site of infection was blood and the patient was diagnosed with Hib type B bacteremia. On an unspecified date, the patient was discharged. [In this study, Ill appearance was defined as documentation of "ill-appearing," "toxic-appearing," poor perfusion including capillary refill time more than 3 seconds, or respiratory distress]. The case was considered for suspected vaccination failure being time to onset unknown. The case was considered as serious due to suspected vaccination failure and hospitalization. Treatment was not reported. Outcome of the event was not reported.  The authors commented "In this retrospective cohort study of 4742 blood cultures obtained from children in the pediatric ED, we found that vaccination status was not associated with bacteremia. Our cohort is composed of children cared for at a pediatric quaternary care facility. All of the cases of S pneumoniae and Hib bacteremia in this study were isolated from subjects who were fully vaccinated. In this study, 5.0% of blood cultures were contaminated and younger infants were significantly more likely to have contaminant growth, likely owing to the greater number of overall cultures obtained. In a systematic review of children presenting with fever without a source, the rate of contaminant growth exceeded that of pathogenic growth in all subjects. Vaccination against S pneumoniae and H influenza has virtually eliminated these pathogens in children aged 2-36 months. Obtaining blood cultures based on vaccination status may not be routinely indicated unless these specific pathogens are of high clinical suspicion or in populations that may lack herd immunity due to low rates of vaccination. In the age of routine vaccinations against S pneumoniae and Hib, clinicians require further guidance on specifically when blood cultures are indicated in pediatric patients younger than the age of 3 years".

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I developed a rash (red splotchy marks on my skin) that started localized under my arms in the arm pit region. I noticed it during my daily shower on 4/9. Basically only my face/head/neck were NOT affected.   Over the next couple of days the rash continued to subside temporarily but then with itching, it would return.   Finally, I am not sure if it is related but I had heart burn like symptoms over night on 4/9 and again on 4/10. That could be a coincidence but I only suffer from heart burn about once every 3 months so it seems strange that I would have it on back to back nights. On evening of initial dose, I had a very sore Arm at the injection site. I feel that it was extremely different from what others describe. I could barely lift the arm without a lot of pain. I wasn't too worried about it as I knew it could only be sore for so long. It faded throughout the next days. On 04/07/21, I woke from a sleep at 4am and as I rolled over, I had a massive wave of dizziness come over me. I thought it was very strange so I decided to sit up, in bed. As soon as I sat up, the room started spinning. It felt as if I were drunk as a skunk. I managed to steady myself and got out of bed and went to the bathroom, all the while fighting the dizziness/vertigo. The dizziness/vertigo has prevailed since then, but at a diminished rate. It is better if I am up and moving and worse if I am sitting/laying around. I've waited almost a week to file this VAER but feel like it needs to be done.
HISTORY: Smoker for 26 years(Pack a day). Quit smoking in 2017.
ALLERGIES: Had an alergic reaction to Relpax once, approx 10 years ago

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I experienced numbness/tingling of my lips and tongue about 10 min after I received the COVID vaccine, no other symptoms concerning for severe allergic reaction.  This side effect lessened after about 4-5 hours, but was still present for at least 24 hours and felt lightheaded for 3-4 days.  I called my primary care physician and allergist regarding this side effect for advice on whether this was related to allergic reaction and they thought it was secondary to the way the vaccine was administered.  The person who administered my vaccine immediately massaged the injection site after injection stating that it was to "get the vaccine into the muscle". I was told by my physicians and the pharmacist at the facility that this was not supposed to happen (the massaging of injection site).  When asked about whether or not this would affect efficacy, one of the pharmacist told me that they were unsure, but maybe would not reach full efficacy.     I am still upset and left with uncertainty that I might not have the same protection at the end of my vaccines

The patient (self) felt a soreness around the site of the injection begin immediately and grow throughout the day. The soreness continued to at least April 12 (at the time of this report). The soreness was immediate unlike a tetanus shot but the pain the following days was 2-3 times less that of a tetanus shot. By 4pm the same day, the patient felt fatigue and tired and had difficulty staying awake. Around 6pm the patient took 200 mg of ibuprofen by mouth because of a strong headache. At 7pm the patient was experiencing the following: headache, warm head to the touch, shivering/shaking,  fatigue, mild aching. The patients pulse was consistent 100-104 bpm. The patients temperature at 8:30pm was 100.4 F. The patient then went to bed at 9pm. Patient had trouble falling asleep due to fever, shaking, aching. The patient slept intermittently until midnight. At midnight, the patient noticed the fever and shaking had ceased but the headache and aching were still strong. The aching was all over the body. The patients eyes hurt to move. The aching was constant and at times was throbbing. At 3am the patient could still not sleep well so he took 650 mg of Acetaminophen by mouth. The patient began to notice some relief approximately 30-60 min after. The patient fell asleep after the relief began and slept soundly til 9:15 am, April 11th. The patient awoke feeling much better. All side effects had stopped with the exception of a feeling of weakness and slight dizziness. The patient was able to carry on normally and took no more medications.
PRIOR_VAX: Simple soreness around injection site

However, the decision was made by the patient to proceed to receive the first dose of Pfizer vaccine. Patient received vaccine at approximately 02:00 pm. Shortly after administration of the vaccine and while in the reaction waiting area, he experienced ?dizziness and difficulty breathing? and requested assistance. Onsite medics state patient leaned his head back and his eyes rolled back in his head. No sign of swelling, itchy, or rash. Vital signs were within normal limit. Paramedic was immediately called at 02:08 pm. EMS arrived at 02:15 pm and departed at 02:20 pm. Paramedics transported non-emergent patient to ED.  ED DX: vasovagal syncope; no signs of anaphylaxis or severe vaccine reaction.  Patient released from emergency department at 03:15 pm with without activity restrictions.

I received the first dose of the Moderna vaccine  at 2:55pm on 4/7.  An hour or two later, I started to get a sore throat.  The sore throat was very painful by the early morning of 4/8.  On 4/8 I went into a doctor to see if I had strep throat because of the level of pain and since I didn't think I could get a sore throat from the vaccine, but he said it was not strep and that it was likely just a side effect of the vaccine.  On 4/8 I also had a fever topping 101.4, fatigue (I slept a lot that day), mental fog, pain at injection site, and all-around body pain.  The sore throat lessened greatly by 4/9, so it clearly wasn't a strep infection and seems it was indeed a side effect of the vaccine.  From 4/9 through 4/11 I had general "cold" symptoms: runny nose, phlegmy, watery eyes, redness and pain at injection site, muscle aches, elevated temperature (not fever), and general fatigue. By 4/12, these symptoms are nearly completely gone.  Some of these symptoms seemed quite strange as side effects from the vaccine, but they started and perfectly paralleled the expected vaccine side-effects, which makes me think they were caused by the vaccine.  I have no reason to think I had another illness at the same time as when I was experiencing these side-effects.  I had had Covid-19 previously (in December 2020; I tested positive and had mild symptoms).  Perhaps having had Covid-19 already provoked these strange side-effects.
OTHER_MEDS: Omega-3 from Fish Oil oral supplement (500mg daily)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After administration of Janssen vaccine 0.5mL, pt reported arm was hurting and he began moving arm.  CMA noticed that continued to shake arm after 5 minutes but patient was alert and oriented x 3.  CMA thought the way he was shaking his arm seemed irregular so she advised pt he would be taken to an observation area for further observation.  Half way to the observation area, pt reported to CMA that he was seeing spots and felt like he was going to get sick.  CMA called for help.  Patient experienced a syncopal event just as he made it to the chair.  Several staff was helping to support patient.  Legs were lifted to another chair.  Patient was not responsive for a short time, very diaphoretic, breathing regular and unlabored.  Patients eyes then rolled upward toward the ceiling and patient's entire body began shaking uncontrollably while staff managed to keep patient from falling to floor from the chair.  Once patient was conscious, he was able to state his name but reported he was very confused and could not think clearly.  He was able to sit upright.  In the meantime while patient was shaking uncontrollably, staff sought urgent care provider to come and see patient.  Patient was then taken over to the urgent care side of the building to evaluate and treat patient.
LAB_DATA: Blood glucose 142 PIV inserted and bolus of 500mL of 0.9% normal saline was administered

Potentially excessive doses. The Registry identified that the record of this patient had received a first dose of vaccine at a different clinic 1 week prior to receiving a first dose of Pfizer at our clinic. The other clinic was doing a community outreach through the Institute and recording giving a vaccine to someone with the same name and date of birth. When I spoke with the patient, who is an employee at our university, she denied receiving a vaccine from anywhere else. The person who received their first dose of vaccine at the other clinic cancelled their second dose appointment. The patient maintained that she had only received one dose so we made the decision to provide her a second dose. It is possible this was a third dose and the patient was not forthcoming about this; it is also possible there was someone else with the same name and birthdate; another possibility is that someone was utilizing this patient's identity to receive the vaccine. We will attempt to follow up to make sure there is not someone else that needs a second dose.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Got the shot at 9:20am on Saturday (April 10th). By the time I sat down to do the 15min waiting period before I could leave. My arm from the back of my shoulder all the way down to around my thumb joint in my hand ached so bad. By around 3pm on the same day, I started to feel really tired and had a pounding migraine. By 4:30p I started to get really cold and everything started to ache. By 6p I was feeling hot but at the same time cold and shivering. My head was pounding. Every muscle ached all over my body, and by every muscle I mean even my eye muscles and pelvic floor muscles. My face had so much sinus pressure that it felt like it could explode. My skin, all over my body, was so sensitive that it hurt to the touch. On top of my skin being sensitive to the touch, off and on my skin would tingle, including the inside of my mouth and tongue. My lymph nodes were swollen enough in my neck that my throat ached.  I was mentally confused and shaking. Everything got bad enough I started crying and hyperventilating. I felt sick to my stomach and felt digestive pain. My entire body felt so heavy. By the time it got to around 8p, my mom finally took my temperature, which at that point I had already been taking Tylenol all day and was no longer shivering, and I had a temperature of 101 degrees F. I finally went to bed around 9p. I was thirsty but my stomach felt sick. I still ached and woke up around 10 times throughout the night either feeling too hot or cold or hurting so bad. At 4am I took a Tylenol because it everything hurt bad enough to able to fall asleep. The next day. I mostly better. I was still tired and a little achy and my lymph nodes under my arm pits were swollen. At this point my lungs felt strange. Harder to breathe than normal.  I was starting to cough. The day after that (today) I have felt fairly normal except I?m coughing and my lungs still feel a little strained. No more aches or fever or anything like that though.
OTHER_MEDS: 5000IU of Vitamin D (taken every day as prescribed by doctor)
HISTORY: IBS, seasonal sinus/allergies, scoliosis, benign essential tremors
ALLERGIES: Possible Chicory Root Allergy. Seasonal Allergies.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Returned home around 4:30 PM from vaccine and felt a bit tired & not hungry for dinner. Iced my arm and took 2 Tylenol as my head began hurting.  I went to bed at 9:00 PM and woke up around 1:00 AM with an excruciating headache and felt nauseous I took 2 more Tylenol, but could not fall back asleep. I felt very nauseous and was unable to go back to sleep. Oddly, I was sitting up wide awake and for a period of about 30 minutes, I began seeing brightly colored images that looked like they were floating in front of me. It was extremely odd as my eyes were open and I was awake. I finally fell back asleep around 5:30 AM and had horrifying vivid nightmares. When I woke up around 8:00 AM my headache was still there and I felt somewhat nauseous but not as bad as during the night.  My headache continued through the day on Saturday and I continued to take Tylenol about every 6 hours. I attempted to go to bed around 9 PM when I experienced horrible chest pain that radiated through my chest and into the left side of my throat. This was frightening because the pain did not let up for 7 to 8 hours, even after taking a Tagamet. I've never suffered from heartburn previously other than when I was 8 months pregnant with twins. I was lucky to have any medication at home and that was only because my husband suffered from heartburn frequently. I finally fell asleep around 6:00 am for just a few hours and woke up feeling tired, but no headache or chest pain. Other than feeling tired, the symptoms appeared to all be gone. On a positive note, my arm never became sore!
HISTORY: Off and on skin rashes and previous multiple skin cancers

5 April 2021, at 14:15: Approximately 45 minutes after my initial Moderna vaccine the left side of my face became freezing cold and numb. The progression was instantaneous yet started deep in my inner left ear and around the outside corner of my left eye and instantly moved up to my forehead (crossing the midline), then down the midline of my face encompassing my left eye, the left side of my nose, lips, roof of my mouth, gums, tongue, back over to my left cheek area all the way to my left ear. Simultaneously, I had a surge of metallic-tasing saliva, and I had a tingling vibration (tingling without the pins-and-needles) in both of my hands and on my left shin, just above my ankle to just below my knee. It all happened so fast that I could not talk and verbalize what was happening, I could only hold up my hand in a STOP position. My airway was open and I did not have any respiratory issues. The numbness in my face was about a 9 out of 10. Very numb, very frozen.   We went back to the vaccination site and I was put under observation for an additional 15-20 minutes. The observation was 100% hands-off?no BP, no pulse ox, no temperature. I was released with the advice that if I developed any breathing difficulties that I was ?to go to the local emergency room.?   5 April 2021, at 19:00. The numbness receded to about a 5 out of 10. I did not have any respiratory issues, but was able to start noticing other parts of my body that were numb: the entire roof of my mouth; my teeth/gums from the midline-left; when I swallowed I noticed that my throat had no sensation on the left side and felt ?smooth?; both deep, inner ears ached without the any sharp pain. I had a massive headache and took 400mg of ibuprofen and went to bed.       6 April 2021, 09:00. After waking I got out of bed and noticed that my left leg was weak. I thought it was the position that I had been sleeping in, yet it did not?and still has not?gone away. The numbness in my face was still present and that it had extended down onto my lower lips and chin. Most of the left side of my face felt like heavy Silly Puddy, it felt swollen and stiff. The outside corner of my left eye, the left side of my nose, forehead creases and ear were stationary and not moving. My blinking felt off, but didn?t look off. I could now tell that the entire left side of my body was markedly weaker than my right side, my balance was off. I could not feel sensation in my chest/lung cavity as I inhaled and exhaled like I could on my right side. I did not have any airway or breathing difficulties. I rested and hydrated.   6 April 2021, 20:00. A rash of itching, burning hives erupted onto my lower left jaw from just outside my lip line and spread along the curve of my lower jaw bone to my hairline. By 22:00 the itch and burning had subsided, but I could feel that it was still there.   7 April 2021, 02:30. I woke up with excruciating, stabbing ear pain in my right inner ear. I took ibuprofen and tried to fall back to sleep.   7 April 2021, 09:00. My face felt increasingly swollen and stiff and the numb/tingling/vibration sensation in my lower left leg began to spread to my inner leg, around to my calf, up and over my knee to my upper thigh; my leg became so weak that it buckled. We spoke to a nurse advice line and she recommended going to the emergency room.   7 April 2021, 15:00.  Dr. saw me. I was given to CT Scan to rule out stroke and an ultrasound to rule out blood clot. I was given the diagnosis of Bell?s Palsy and was put on antiviral medication; I declined the steroids because they increase my allergic response reactions.  11 April 2021, 18:00. My face started to swell up over my left eye, left cheek, left ear and over to my right cheek. It did not restrict my airway. I went to bed.   12 April 2021, 17:30. My face?midline to left?is still numb; the left side of my body?especially my left leg?is still markedly weaker than my right; I get winded easily; I tire easily; my mouth still tastes metallic; I still have inner earaches on both sides; my eyes are extremely dry.   I am also a yoga instructor. I know my body. I was perfectly able-bodied and healthy at 13:20 on 5 April 2021, 45 minutes later my world unraveled and no one knows how long it will last.
LAB_DATA: 7 April 2021:  CT Scan NEGATIVE to rule out stroke; ultrasound NEGATIVE to rule out blood clot. Diagnosis: Bell's Palsy brought on by the Moderna vaccine.

4/10/21 ER HPI: 82 y.o. female who presents to the Emergency Department by paramedics from a local nursing home.  The patient is an 82-year-old female with a known history of end-stage renal disease, diabetes, and coronary artery disease.  She presented to the emergency room after being transported from a local nursing home.  Apparently, the patient was acting a little bit more confused than normal and she was looking more short of breath than normal.  The nursing home nurse stated that her oxygen saturations were in the upper 80s without oxygen and the patient looked visibly more short of breath than normal.  Because of this, the nursing home made the decision to send the patient in.  When paramedics arrived at the nursing home they placed 2 L of oxygen on her and her oxygen saturations went up into the high 90s.  The patient does dialysis on Monday, Wednesday, Friday.  She did not miss a dialysis treatment this week.  The patient has had her coronavirus (COVID-19) vaccine and several months ago did have coronavirus (COVID-19) at the local nursing home.  The patient does have mild dementia and so is somewhat of an unreliable historian.  Transferred to pleural effusion

I fell strait forward, onto my stomach with a large crash. The rest of the day, I did feel fatigue, joint pain in my knees and then chills/hot flashes later in the day/evening. The next morning (Friday) I woke up with a scratchy throat but felt fine the rest of the day.  I  have never fainted in the past. I don't know what would bring that on.  I also have not had that feeling or any fainting spells since that incident. My wife came home about 8am out of concern.

My vaccine was on Monday morning, had the normal reactions, being very cold and a bad headache for about 36 hours.  The day after the vaccine, my heart started racing like crazy.  My left side of my neck and behind my ear hurt very much.  I have a blood pressure cuff and it would not register.  I was extremely scared and the beating of my heart was also noticeable through my clothing.  The following  Wed. 4/7 morning at 5am, the cuff finally registered and my blood pressure was 158/86.  I came to work on Wednesday 2 hours later and had the school nurse take my pressure and it was 150/80.  About 4 hours later it was 138/76.  The neck/ear pain was gone that morning.

I received my second dose when I was 17 weeks pregnant. About 12 hours after receiving the shot, I started running a fever, feeling much more fatigued than usual, experiencing sweats and chills, and all-over body aches. My symptoms very much felt like the flu. I took extra-strength Tylenol every 4 hours and monitored my temperature.  Approximately 26 hours after my shot, my temperature continued to rise and no longer responded to the extra-strength Tylenol. At its highest, my temperature was 101.9. If I had not been pregnant, I would not have worried or gone to the emergency room. However, since my fever was no longer responding to the extra-strength Tylenol, and since it was a Sunday and my doctor's office was closed, I went to the ER so they could monitor my temperature. Unfortunately, I sat in the ER for 4 hours before I was seen by a physician. I monitored my temperature myself during this time, which remained 100.0--100.7, if I remember those numbers correctly. By that time, my fever had subsided. For the next 2 days, I still exhibited all other flu-like symptoms described above, except the fever.
LAB_DATA: Physician examination and doppler for baby's heart rate; temperature check; blood pressure and oxygen level check. All tests came back within normal limits.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client reported prior to vaccination, that it is common for him to become faint and possibly "pass out" when receiving injections, having blood draws completed, and IVs started.  Verified that client was feeling well and had eaten breakfast and was hydrated prior to injection.  Client sitting in chair and tolerated injection well.  About 5 minutes after injection given, client reported that he was feeling faint.  Client was clammy and pale, and lost consciousness for about 30 seconds. Wife present and held his head and stood next to him in the chair.  Client did not fall, and stayed seated in the chair.  He slowly regained consciousness, and when able to sit and speak, client was offered water, which he accepted.  VS collected - BP sitting in RUE - 108/78, P - 64, R - 16, O2 sats - 96%.  Client started to regain color, and report that he was feeling better.   Granola bar offered and client ate.  Wife reported that this is a common event for client, when having blood drawn, IVs started, or injections given.  Client states that he has "passed out many times before." Client stayed seated in chair, with RN and wife in room with him.  By 0945, client states that he was feeling "back to normal."  No s/s of allergic reaction.  Wife to drive home and stay with husband for the rest of the day.  Discussed s/s of allergic reaction, and other s/s that require immediate medical attention.  Wife and client verbalized understanding.
PRIOR_VAX: many events like this, with previous injections, IV starts, or blood draws
